Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's start class.\N{\rChinese}好的，开始上课吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.32,0:00:08.42,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to review very quickly what we did last class.\N{\rChinese}我会快速回顾上节课的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.70,0:00:13.30,English,,0,0,0,,So last class we learned about monotheism,\N{\rChinese}上节课我们学习了单神论。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.52,0:00:15.50,English,,0,0,0,,which\N{\rChinese}哪一个
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.50,0:00:19.02,English,,0,0,0,,is the idea of one true God.\N{\rChinese}是一个真神的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.36,0:00:21.22,English,,0,0,0,,And as I said last class,\N{\rChinese}正如我上节课所说，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:26.92,English,,0,0,0,,this marked an intellectual revolution in human history.\N{\rChinese}这标志着人类历史上的一次知识革命。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.92,0:00:31.46,English,,0,0,0,,And for monotheism, we developed three new ideas,\N{\rChinese}而在单神论中，我们发展了三种新思想，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:34.56,English,,0,0,0,,which are money,\N{\rChinese}它们是货币、
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.76,0:00:38.40,English,,0,0,0,,individual,\N{\rChinese}个体，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.86,0:00:43.16,English,,0,0,0,,and the nation state.\N{\rChinese}和民族国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.04,0:00:48.96,English,,0,0,0,,It's important to note that\N{\rChinese}重要的是要注意到
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.96,0:00:52.18,English,,0,0,0,,these ideas have always existed in human history,\N{\rChinese}这些思想在人类历史中一直存在，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.38,0:00:56.90,English,,0,0,0,,but with monotheism, these ideas became the dominant paradigm.\N{\rChinese}但在单神论出现后，这些思想成为主导范式。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.92,0:00:58.36,English,,0,0,0,,And together,\N{\rChinese}并且它们一起，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.68,0:01:01.68,English,,0,0,0,,they will give us modernity\N{\rChinese}它们将为我们带来现代性
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.68,0:01:04.98,English,,0,0,0,,and create the world that\N{\rChinese}并创造我们今天所处的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.98,0:01:07.06,English,,0,0,0,,we live in today.\N{\rChinese}我们正生活其中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.76,0:01:10.86,English,,0,0,0,,So that's what we discussed last class.\N{\rChinese}所以这就是我们上节课讨论的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.18,0:01:13.78,English,,0,0,0,,And remember last class, we also discussed that\N{\rChinese}记得上节课，我们还讨论了这一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.78,0:01:17.40,English,,0,0,0,,this created a lot of problems for us.\N{\rChinese}这给我们带来了很多问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.46,0:01:20.08,English,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of benefits, but there are also a lot of consequences.\N{\rChinese}有许多好处，也有许多后果。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.10,0:01:26.19,English,,0,0,0,,So we're going to continue the story of humanity today.\N{\rChinese}于是我们继续讲述当今人类的故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:30.20,English,,0,0,0,,And today, I want to focus on a very specific question.\N{\rChinese}今天，我要聚焦一个非常具体的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.78,0:01:34.54,English,,0,0,0,,Why do societies rise and why do they fall?\N{\rChinese}为什么社会会兴起，又会衰落？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.10,0:01:39.24,English,,0,0,0,,And I know that\N{\rChinese}我知道
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.24,0:01:43.98,English,,0,0,0,,these first few classes may seem abstract\N{\rChinese}这前几节课看起来可能抽象
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.98,0:01:46.06,English,,0,0,0,,and theoretical, but that's because\N{\rChinese}并且理论化，但那是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.06,0:01:51.60,English,,0,0,0,,we're developing the ethical models in order to better understand our world.\N{\rChinese}我们正在制定伦理模型，以更好地理解我们的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.78,0:01:55.78,English,,0,0,0,,So as we move on, we'll start looking at very concrete examples.\N{\rChinese}于是我们继续前进，开始研究非常具体的例子
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.92,0:02:00.22,English,,0,0,0,,But for the first few classes, please be patient.\N{\rChinese}但在前几节课里，请耐心等待。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.42,0:02:04.72,English,,0,0,0,,We are going to develop a theory to understand the world.\N{\rChinese}我们将构建理论来理解世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:08.10,English,,0,0,0,,So let's discuss societies,\N{\rChinese}于是我们来讨论社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.42,0:02:11.48,English,,0,0,0,,why they rise and\N{\rChinese}为什么它们崛起
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.48,0:02:13.82,English,,0,0,0,,why they decline.\N{\rChinese}为什么它们衰落
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.98,0:02:21.10,English,,0,0,0,,Now, unfortunately, we live in a world in decline.\N{\rChinese}现在不幸的是，我们正处于一个衰落的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:25.66,English,,0,0,0,,So there are lots of signs that\N{\rChinese}于是有许多迹象
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.66,0:02:26.90,English,,0,0,0,,the world is in decline.\N{\rChinese}世界正处于衰落之中
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.90,0:02:29.02,English,,0,0,0,,What are these signs?\N{\rChinese}这些迹象是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.44,0:02:31.22,English,,0,0,0,,Shout out some signs.\N{\rChinese}列举一些迹象。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.38,0:02:34.94,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, very good.\N{\rChinese}好的，很好。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.10,0:02:38.34,English,,0,0,0,,So you have conflict and wars.\N{\rChinese}于是你就有冲突和战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.78,0:02:42.38,English,,0,0,0,,You look at the situation in Ukraine.\N{\rChinese}你看看乌克兰的局势。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.72,0:02:44.28,English,,0,0,0,,Look at the situation in the Middle East.\N{\rChinese}再看看中东的局势。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:47.94,English,,0,0,0,,But also, you may have seen the news\N{\rChinese}另外，你可能已经看到新闻。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.94,0:02:51.88,English,,0,0,0,,and you have seen conflicts arising in Southeast Asia, Thailand,\N{\rChinese}以及你已经看到东南亚的冲突在泰国、缅甸出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.34,0:02:56.88,English,,0,0,0,,Myanmar. Also, Trump is about to sell his country.\N{\rChinese}另外，特朗普正准备把他的国家卖掉。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.88,0:02:59.80,English,,0,0,0,,He's about to send U.S. troops to Mexico and Venezuela.\N{\rChinese}他正准备把美军派往墨西哥和委内瑞拉。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.12,0:03:01.74,English,,0,0,0,,So we live in a world of conflict.\N{\rChinese}于是我们生活在冲突的世界里。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.38,0:03:04.62,English,,0,0,0,,And that tells us that the world is in decline.\N{\rChinese}这说明世界正处于衰落之中。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.62,0:03:06.90,English,,0,0,0,,What are some other signs?\N{\rChinese}还有哪些其他迹象？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.78,0:03:09.78,English,,0,0,0,,Environment. Good, yes.\N{\rChinese}环境。好的，没错。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.94,0:03:11.14,English,,0,0,0,,So you have climate change.\N{\rChinese}所以你有气候变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.96,0:03:20.50,English,,0,0,0,,We are putting too much pressure on the environment.\N{\rChinese}我们对环境施加过大压力。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:22.98,English,,0,0,0,,So the air, the water,\N{\rChinese}于是空气、河水、土地都变得更有毒。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.12,0:03:25.78,English,,0,0,0,,the land is becoming much more toxic.\N{\rChinese}好的。还有什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.88,0:03:29.84,English,,0,0,0,,Good. What else? Good, yes.\N{\rChinese}好的，没错。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.04,0:03:33.86,English,,0,0,0,,Unemployment is going up.\N{\rChinese}失业率在上升。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.18,0:03:38.98,English,,0,0,0,,But not only that, but people's attitude towards work is declining.\N{\rChinese}但不止于此，大家对工作的态度也在下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.58,0:03:41.44,English,,0,0,0,,We live in an age when\N{\rChinese}我们正处于一个时代…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:44.86,English,,0,0,0,,people don't take work that seriously.\N{\rChinese}人们不再把工作当回事。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:47.16,English,,0,0,0,,People are not as enthusiastic.\N{\rChinese}人们的热情不再那么高。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.44,0:03:50.40,English,,0,0,0,,They're not as motivated to work hard as before.\N{\rChinese}他们不像以前那样有劲儿去努力工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.64,0:03:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,We call this in China the Bailan age, right?\N{\rChinese}我们把这叫做中国的摆烂时代，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.72,0:03:58.04,English,,0,0,0,,The age of Bailan, meaning let it rot.\N{\rChinese}摆烂时代，意为让它腐烂。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.26,0:04:00.92,English,,0,0,0,,Like, who cares? Don't take things too seriously.\N{\rChinese}比如，谁在乎？别把事儿想得太认真。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.64,0:04:06.52,English,,0,0,0,,In America, the term is called quite quitting.\N{\rChinese}在美国，这个词叫做“相当放弃”。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.20,0:04:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,You pretend to work, but you're not really working.\N{\rChinese}你表面上在工作，却并没有真正工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.20,0:04:11.20,English,,0,0,0,,What are some other signs?\N{\rChinese}还有哪些其他迹象？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.12,0:04:19.52,English,,0,0,0,,So also, you have lower birth rate.\N{\rChinese}于是，你的出生率也下降了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.66,0:04:22.86,English,,0,0,0,,And this is a very important sign, right?\N{\rChinese}这也是一个非常重要的标志，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.00,0:04:24.70,English,,0,0,0,,Because if you think about it,\N{\rChinese}因为如果你想想看，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.70,0:04:28.62,English,,0,0,0,,if young people refuse to get married\N{\rChinese}如果年轻人不结婚并且有孩子，最终世界就会消亡，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.62,0:04:33.08,English,,0,0,0,,and have babies, eventually the world is going to die off, right?\N{\rChinese}于是这实际上是一个非常重要的标志，说明世界正在衰落。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.32,0:04:37.84,English,,0,0,0,,So this is actually a very important sign that the world is in decline.\N{\rChinese}So this is actually a very important sign that the world is in decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.16,0:04:43.16,English,,0,0,0,,And we're seeing this happen throughout the entire world in all societies.\N{\rChinese}我们在全世界各个社会中都看到这种情况发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.90,0:04:47.82,English,,0,0,0,,The only exception is Israel and Georgia.\N{\rChinese}唯一例外是以色列和格鲁吉亚。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:50.84,English,,0,0,0,,But these are very small, rare cases.\N{\rChinese}但这些只是很小很少的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.00,0:04:52.00,English,,0,0,0,,For most societies,\N{\rChinese}对大多数社会而言，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.30,0:04:57.24,English,,0,0,0,,there's rapid decline in birth rate.\N{\rChinese}出生率迅速下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:04:58.78,English,,0,0,0,,What are some other signs?\N{\rChinese}还有哪些其他迹象？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.94,0:05:04.08,English,,0,0,0,,You see a lower\N{\rChinese}你会看到生活水平下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.08,0:05:09.00,English,,0,0,0,,standard of living.\N{\rChinese}并且这意味着通胀。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.48,0:05:13.86,English,,0,0,0,,And all this means is that inflation, right?\N{\rChinese}And all this means isthat inflation, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.04,0:05:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,So people make less money, and they can afford less.\N{\rChinese}于是人们收入减少，消费也随之减少。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:20.80,English,,0,0,0,,Prices go up, but people's wages go down.\N{\rChinese}物价上涨，工资却下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.80,0:05:24.58,English,,0,0,0,,So that's another sign of decline.\N{\rChinese}这又是衰落的又一标志。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.00,0:05:27.46,English,,0,0,0,,What are some other signs?\N{\rChinese}还有哪些其他迹象？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.14,0:05:33.76,English,,0,0,0,,Now it's like diabetes or high blood pressure.\N{\rChinese}现在就像糖尿病或高血压。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.68,0:05:38.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. You also see higher stress, right?\N{\rChinese}好的，你也会看到更高的压力，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.60,0:05:42.66,English,,0,0,0,,Higher stress, people feel more anxious.\N{\rChinese}更高的压力，人们更焦虑。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.74,0:05:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,People feel more depressed. People feel more stressed.\N{\rChinese}人们更抑郁，压力更大。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.78,0:05:47.48,English,,0,0,0,,Emotionally, they feel drained.\N{\rChinese}情感上，他们感到精疲力竭。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:53.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, what else? Okay,\N{\rChinese}好的，另外还有什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.42,0:05:55.52,English,,0,0,0,,people are less optimistic, right?\N{\rChinese}人们的乐观度下降了，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.02,0:05:59.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Greater pessimism.\N{\rChinese}好的，悲观情绪更浓。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.10,0:06:07.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Also, this is really important, is the idea of debt.\N{\rChinese}好的，另外，这个债务的概念真的很重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.08,0:06:13.18,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Both public and private.\N{\rChinese}对吗？既有公共债务也有私人债务。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.92,0:06:19.50,English,,0,0,0,,There are lots of governments around the world that are facing a fiscal crisis.\N{\rChinese}世界各地有许多政府正面临财政危机。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.80,0:06:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,A fiscal crisis just means that\N{\rChinese}财政危机只是意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.68,0:06:25.32,English,,0,0,0,,they spend more than they take in in tax revenue.\N{\rChinese}他们的支出超过税收收入。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.96,0:06:29.96,English,,0,0,0,,There are many families in China,\N{\rChinese}中国有许多家庭。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.06,0:06:35.80,English,,0,0,0,,in the United States, throughout the world that are heavily in debt. Okay, so\N{\rChinese}在美国，世界各地都深陷债务。好了，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.80,0:06:41.24,English,,0,0,0,,debt is a huge issue for the world today.\N{\rChinese}债务是当今世界的重大问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.52,0:06:45.46,English,,0,0,0,,Also, lower cohesion\N{\rChinese}此外，凝聚力下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.46,0:06:47.70,English,,0,0,0,,and trust.\N{\rChinese}和信任。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:50.58,English,,0,0,0,,And what this means is that\N{\rChinese}而这意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.58,0:06:53.82,English,,0,0,0,,people no longer trust each\N{\rChinese}人们不再信任
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.82,0:06:56.72,English,,0,0,0,,other as they did before.\N{\rChinese}其他如他们以前所做的那样。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.34,0:06:59.04,English,,0,0,0,,Society is less cohesive.\N{\rChinese}社会凝聚力下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.68,0:07:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,If you see, if you walk on the street and\N{\rChinese}如果你看到，如果你走在街上…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:07.58,English,,0,0,0,,you see a man on the street bleeding or hurt,\N{\rChinese}你看到街上有人流血或受伤，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.78,0:07:09.38,English,,0,0,0,,you're less likely to help him.\N{\rChinese}你就不太可能去帮他。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.88,0:07:13.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, and this is very true not only in China\N{\rChinese}好的，这点在中国也很真实。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.28,0:07:16.26,English,,0,0,0,,but also elsewhere as well.\N{\rChinese}也在其他地方一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.36,0:07:17.58,English,,0,0,0,,So lower trust issues.\N{\rChinese}于是信任度下降。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.58,0:07:19.22,English,,0,0,0,,What are some other signs?\N{\rChinese}还有哪些其他迹象？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.64,0:07:26.70,English,,0,0,0,,Disease. Okay, greater disease, yeah.\N{\rChinese}疾病。好的，疾病增多了。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:28.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, increase in disease.\N{\rChinese}好的，疾病增多。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.74,0:07:32.58,English,,0,0,0,,People are less healthy than before.\N{\rChinese}人们的健康状况比以前差。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.80,0:07:34.36,English,,0,0,0,,People are more stressed than before.\N{\rChinese}人们比以前更紧张。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.66,0:07:35.96,English,,0,0,0,,People are less optimistic.\N{\rChinese}人们更不乐观。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.42,0:07:41.34,English,,0,0,0,,So we can go on and on and on.\N{\rChinese}于是我们可以继续继续继续。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.62,0:07:47.50,English,,0,0,0,,Because the signs of rapid social decline are too many.\N{\rChinese}因为快速社会衰退的迹象太多了。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.54,0:07:52.14,English,,0,0,0,,Now, these are signs of decline.\N{\rChinese}现在，这些就是衰退的迹象。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:56.98,English,,0,0,0,,Well, if we look at rise, then obviously it's the opposite, right?\N{\rChinese}好吧，如果我们看上升，显然就是相反的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.48,0:07:59.58,English,,0,0,0,,People are much more willing to trust each other.\N{\rChinese}人们更愿意互相信任。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.72,0:08:01.96,English,,0,0,0,,Rather than going into debt, people will save money.\N{\rChinese}人们不再借债，而是存钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:05.80,English,,0,0,0,,People are healthier. People are much more optimistic.\N{\rChinese}人们更健康，更乐观。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.72,0:08:08.68,English,,0,0,0,,People are\N{\rChinese}人们在
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.68,0:08:14.16,English,,0,0,0,,having lots\N{\rChinese}有很多
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:15.84,English,,0,0,0,,and lots of babies, right?\N{\rChinese}并且有很多宝宝，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.42,0:08:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. People are employed.\N{\rChinese}好的。人们有工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:26.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So these are all signs\N{\rChinese}好的？所以这些都是迹象
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.68,0:08:30.28,English,,0,0,0,,that society is in decline.\N{\rChinese}表明社会正在衰落。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.56,0:08:31.98,English,,0,0,0,,The rise, it's the opposite.\N{\rChinese}上升，正好相反。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.50,0:08:36.06,English,,0,0,0,,Also, another sign of decline that's very important\N{\rChinese}另外，还有一个非常重要的衰落迹象
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.06,0:08:40.66,English,,0,0,0,,that doesn't really happen in China, what happens in the Western world is immigration.\N{\rChinese}在中国并不常见，西方出现的是移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.22,0:08:45.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Immigration.\N{\rChinese}好的？移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:48.94,English,,0,0,0,,Immigration is a huge issue in the Western world,\N{\rChinese}移民是西方的一个大问题，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:52.34,English,,0,0,0,,and we will discuss immigration in future classes.\N{\rChinese}我们将在后续课程中讨论移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.66,0:08:56.04,English,,0,0,0,,But immigration is a sign of decline because\N{\rChinese}但移民是衰落的迹象，因为它减少了凝聚力。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.04,0:08:58.80,English,,0,0,0,,it reduces cohesion.\N{\rChinese}好？它还降低了生活水平。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.84,0:09:06.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And it also reduces the standard of living. Okay?\N{\rChinese}好？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.70,0:09:12.68,English,,0,0,0,,Another sign of decline is also housing prices.\N{\rChinese}另一个衰落的迹象是房价。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.60,0:09:19.68,English,,0,0,0,,So, people can no longer afford to buy a house.\N{\rChinese}于是人们再也买不起房子。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.92,0:09:21.18,English,,0,0,0,,This is true in China.\N{\rChinese}这在中国也是真的。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.30,0:09:23.36,English,,0,0,0,,Young people can no longer afford to buy a house.\N{\rChinese}年轻人再也买不起房子。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.48,0:09:25.76,English,,0,0,0,,But it's also true throughout the world.\N{\rChinese}但这在全球也同样。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.98,0:09:30.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It's really hard for young people to get by.\N{\rChinese}年轻人真的很难过活。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.18,0:09:32.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.56,0:09:35.92,English,,0,0,0,,Also, fiscal crisis.\N{\rChinese}还有，财政危机。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.18,0:09:37.86,English,,0,0,0,,Right? We talked about this. But\N{\rChinese}对吧？我们说过这个。但
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.86,0:09:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,the idea of fiscal crisis is the government cannot afford a lot of public,\N{\rChinese}财政危机的概念是政府无法承担大量公共支出。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.30,0:09:45.48,English,,0,0,0,,public expenditures.\N{\rChinese}未来，或许多五、十年后，…。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:49.40,English,,0,0,0,,In the future, maybe five, ten years from now,\N{\rChinese}…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.24,0:09:52.44,English,,0,0,0,,pension will be a huge problem for governments.\N{\rChinese}养老金将成为政府的巨大问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.46,0:09:56.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, these are all signs of rapid decline.\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以，这些都是快速衰退的迹象。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.12,0:09:58.86,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Now, having done this,\N{\rChinese}好了。现在，完成了这一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.46,0:10:02.04,English,,0,0,0,,what I'm going to do now is go\N{\rChinese}我现在要做的事是去梳理一些理论，解释为什么会出现这种情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.04,0:10:06.34,English,,0,0,0,,over some theories as to why this is happening.\N{\rChinese}世界为何衰退？】
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.84,0:10:09.68,English,,0,0,0,,Why is the world in decline?\N{\rChinese}Why is the worldin decline?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.58,0:10:13.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And there are lots and lots of theories.\N{\rChinese}好的？还有很多很多理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.30,0:10:16.84,English,,0,0,0,,But I will present three theories to you\N{\rChinese}但我会给你介绍三个我觉得有趣的理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.84,0:10:19.38,English,,0,0,0,,that I think are interesting.\N{\rChinese}that I think areinteresting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.70,0:10:28.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The first is the idea of financialization. And\N{\rChinese}好的？第一条是金融化的概念。且
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.24,0:10:32.42,English,,0,0,0,,this theory is proposed\N{\rChinese}这个理论是由一位经济学家提出的。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:35.14,English,,0,0,0,,by an economist,\N{\rChinese}by an economist,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.52,0:10:38.50,English,,0,0,0,,a French economist named Thomas Piketty.\N{\rChinese}一位名叫托马斯·皮凯蒂的法国经济学家。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:43.16,English,,0,0,0,,Piketty. Okay? And he wrote a book called Capital.\N{\rChinese}皮凯蒂。好的吗？他写了一本叫《资本》 的书。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.30,0:10:45.28,English,,0,0,0,,Capital in the 21st Century.\N{\rChinese}《21 世纪的资本》。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.20,0:10:48.12,English,,0,0,0,,It is a fantastic book.\N{\rChinese}这本书很精彩。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:52.12,English,,0,0,0,,You don't have to read the book, but if you have a chance, you should definitely pick it up.\N{\rChinese}不必一定读，但若有机会，最好去拿起读一读。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.18,0:10:54.80,English,,0,0,0,,Because it is a very easy but\N{\rChinese}因为它非常容易但
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:57.04,English,,0,0,0,,very illuminating read.\N{\rChinese}非常有启发性的阅读。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.58,0:11:00.60,English,,0,0,0,,And what he argues is\N{\rChinese}而他所论证的是
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.60,0:11:04.06,English,,0,0,0,,that what happens in society is\N{\rChinese}社会中发生的事是
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.06,0:11:09.26,English,,0,0,0,,that capitalism transitions from face to face to face.\N{\rChinese}资本主义从一个面向另一个面转移。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.46,0:11:11.98,English,,0,0,0,,In the beginning, you have consumer.\N{\rChinese}一开始，你就有消费者。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.32,0:11:15.70,English,,0,0,0,,Capitalism. Meaning that\N{\rChinese}资本主义。其含义是。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.70,0:11:20.44,English,,0,0,0,,what the society is trying to do is create goods\N{\rChinese}社会所做的事是制造消费者想买的商品。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.44,0:11:22.18,English,,0,0,0,,that consumers want to buy.\N{\rChinese}这是一段快速财富生成的时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.52,0:11:28.60,English,,0,0,0,,This is an era of rapid wealth generation. Then\N{\rChinese}This is an era of rapidwealth generation. Then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.60,0:11:34.16,English,,0,0,0,,you move into financial capitalism,\N{\rChinese}你进入金融资本主义，[184]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.50,0:11:37.60,English,,0,0,0,,which is a period of investment.\N{\rChinese}这是一段投资时期。[185]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.60,0:11:40.74,English,,0,0,0,,Rather than build factories,\N{\rChinese}不再建造工厂，而是……[186]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.94,0:11:45.52,English,,0,0,0,,you put the money into the stock market.\N{\rChinese}你把钱投入股市。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.62,0:11:48.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好的？那么，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.92,0:11:51.90,English,,0,0,0,,you're trying to generate as much money as possible.\N{\rChinese}你正努力把钱做得尽可能多。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.20,0:11:55.92,English,,0,0,0,,But what we discussed last class that's very important is wealth\N{\rChinese}但我们上节课讨论的非常重要的内容是财富
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:11:57.98,English,,0,0,0,,and money are not the same thing.\N{\rChinese}和钱不是同一回事。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.58,0:12:00.66,English,,0,0,0,,So, in the first phase, consumer capitalism,\N{\rChinese}所以，在第一阶段，消费资本主义中。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.96,0:12:03.64,English,,0,0,0,,you focus on the generation of wealth.\N{\rChinese}你专注于财富的生成。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:07.58,English,,0,0,0,,In financial capitalism, you focus on the generation of money.\N{\rChinese}在金融资本主义中，你专注于钱的生成。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.58,0:12:08.96,English,,0,0,0,,And then\N{\rChinese}然后呢。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.96,0:12:12.46,English,,0,0,0,,you move on to monopoly capitalism,\N{\rChinese}你进入了垄断资本主义的阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.84,0:12:13.98,English,,0,0,0,,which is where\N{\rChinese}在这里，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.98,0:12:16.28,English,,0,0,0,,just a few\N{\rChinese}仅仅是几家
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.28,0:12:19.98,English,,0,0,0,,companies control everything.\N{\rChinese}公司掌控一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.42,0:12:23.62,English,,0,0,0,,And we live in an era of monopoly capitalism.\N{\rChinese}我们正处于垄断资本主义时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:25.74,English,,0,0,0,,And this happens because\N{\rChinese}这之所以发生是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.74,0:12:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,it is much more profitable\N{\rChinese}对公司来说，成为垄断比相互竞争更有利可图。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.64,0:12:32.44,English,,0,0,0,,for companies to be monopolies than\N{\rChinese}对公司来说，成为垄断比相互竞争更有利可图。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.44,0:12:34.44,English,,0,0,0,,to be in competition with each other.\N{\rChinese}对公司来说，成为垄断比相互竞争更有利可图。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.66,0:12:36.26,English,,0,0,0,,Financial capitalism...\N{\rChinese}金融资本主义…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.58,0:12:40.32,English,,0,0,0,,is looking to create as much money as possible, not as much wealth.\N{\rChinese}它正在寻求创造尽可能多的钱，而不是尽可能多的财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.74,0:12:45.34,English,,0,0,0,,And so, a few companies come to dominate, become monopolies.\N{\rChinese}于是，少数公司崛起，成为垄断。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.46,0:12:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,And that's the age we live in today.\N{\rChinese}而这就是我们今天所处的时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.24,0:12:51.26,English,,0,0,0,,Now, why is this important?\N{\rChinese}现在，为什么这很重要？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.68,0:12:54.32,English,,0,0,0,,It's important because...\N{\rChinese}重要的原因是……
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.28,0:12:56.88,English,,0,0,0,,when we make this transition,\N{\rChinese}当我们完成这一步转变时，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.56,0:13:01.74,English,,0,0,0,,people are no longer focused on working hard.\N{\rChinese}人们不再专注于勤劳工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.32,0:13:04.20,English,,0,0,0,,They're only focused on speculating.\N{\rChinese}他们只专注于投机。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.34,0:13:07.42,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So, let me give you an example.\N{\rChinese}好的？那我给你举个例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.98,0:13:13.24,English,,0,0,0,,Let's just say I'm an entrepreneur.\N{\rChinese}假设我是个创业者。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.56,0:13:15.66,English,,0,0,0,,And I want to make as much money as possible.\N{\rChinese}我想尽可能赚大钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.64,0:13:19.38,English,,0,0,0,,Well, what I do is I build a factory.\N{\rChinese}好吧，我的做法是建个工厂。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:22.66,English,,0,0,0,,When I build a factory, I'm creating real wealth.\N{\rChinese}当我建工厂时，我在创造真正的财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.88,0:13:27.48,English,,0,0,0,,Because a factory requires you to hire workers.\N{\rChinese}因为工厂需要雇佣工人。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.72,0:13:29.52,English,,0,0,0,,It requires you to build technology.\N{\rChinese}它需要你去研发技术。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.80,0:13:32.74,English,,0,0,0,,It requires you to build goods that people want to buy.\N{\rChinese}它需要你制造人们想买的商品。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.68,0:13:36.76,English,,0,0,0,,But after I build a factory and I make a lot of money,\N{\rChinese}但当我建好工厂并赚到很多钱后，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.56,0:13:41.82,English,,0,0,0,,I want to take this money and let it grow as fast as possible.\N{\rChinese}我想把这笔钱投入，让它尽快增长。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.94,0:13:43.74,English,,0,0,0,,So, I put it in a stock market.\N{\rChinese}于是，我把它投进股市。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.54,0:13:47.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's just how people behave.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是人们的常规操作。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.92,0:13:50.90,English,,0,0,0,,The problem is that if too many people do\N{\rChinese}问题是如果太多人都这么做，结果就没人真正工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.90,0:13:53.40,English,,0,0,0,,that, then no one's really working.\N{\rChinese}没人真正创造经济中的真实财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.64,0:13:58.18,English,,0,0,0,,No one's creating real wealth in the economy.\N{\rChinese}No one's creating realwealth in the economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.06,0:14:01.76,English,,0,0,0,,The other problem is that...\N{\rChinese}另一个问题是……
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.76,0:14:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,because of the way capitalism is set up,\N{\rChinese}因为资本主义的设定方式，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.72,0:14:09.70,English,,0,0,0,,if everyone's putting the money in a stock market, the stock market grows too fast.\N{\rChinese}如果大家都把钱投进股市，股市就会增长得太快。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.14,0:14:13.34,English,,0,0,0,,And the real economy does not grow that fast.\N{\rChinese}而实体经济并不会这么快增长。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.68,0:14:15.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the difference is stark.\N{\rChinese}好的？差距很明显。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,Thomas Piketty spent a lot of time going over income tax.\N{\rChinese}托马斯·皮凯蒂花了很多时间研究所得税。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.52,0:14:23.82,English,,0,0,0,,Just looking at how much tax people paid.\N{\rChinese}只看人们缴纳的税额。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.12,0:14:25.78,English,,0,0,0,,He did a lot of statistical analysis.\N{\rChinese}他做了大量统计分析。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.10,0:14:31.32,English,,0,0,0,,And what he discovered is the real economy in late -stage capitalism\N{\rChinese}他发现的是真正经济在后期资本主义中的表现。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:32.84,English,,0,0,0,,will grow about 2%.\N{\rChinese}将增长约2%。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:38.08,English,,0,0,0,,The financial economy will grow at 5%.\N{\rChinese}金融经济将增长5%。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.10,0:14:42.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And this is really key.\N{\rChinese}好的吗？这点很关键。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:45.86,English,,0,0,0,,What this is telling us is that if you have a million dollars,\N{\rChinese}这句话告诉我们，如果你有一百万美元，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.55,0:14:48.88,English,,0,0,0,,you could choose to go and open a restaurant,\N{\rChinese}你可以选择去开一家餐馆，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.12,0:14:51.44,English,,0,0,0,,or you could choose to invest in the stock market.\N{\rChinese}或者你可以选择去投资股市。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.80,0:14:53.84,English,,0,0,0,,If you open a restaurant,\N{\rChinese}如果你开一家餐馆，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:14:58.44,English,,0,0,0,,you will make at most $20,000 a year.\N{\rChinese}你一年最多能赚两万美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:03.30,English,,0,0,0,,But if you were to put it in the stock market, you would make $50,000 a year.\N{\rChinese}如果你把钱投进股市，一年能赚五万美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.76,0:15:06.36,English,,0,0,0,,So everyone's going to put all the money in the stock market,\N{\rChinese}于是大家都把钱投入股市，于是股市就能上涨。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.99,0:15:09.62,English,,0,0,0,,which allows for the stock market to increase.\N{\rChinese}但实体经济并没有改善。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.98,0:15:13.40,English,,0,0,0,,But the real economy is not improving.\N{\rChinese}But the real economy is not improving.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.86,0:15:18.00,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you have all these issues arise.\N{\rChinese}于是就出现了这些问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.95,0:15:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,Greater unemployment, greater debt.\N{\rChinese}失业率上升，债务增加。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.87,0:15:23.42,English,,0,0,0,,No one's really working.\N{\rChinese}没人真正在工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.18,0:15:27.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So that's the idea of financialization.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是金融化的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.18,0:15:30.62,English,,0,0,0,,And what Piketty argues is that\N{\rChinese}而皮凯蒂所说的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.62,0:15:33.40,English,,0,0,0,,this is just a natural cycle.\N{\rChinese}这只是一个自然循环。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.72,0:15:36.86,English,,0,0,0,,This is just a natural byproduct of capitalism.\N{\rChinese}这只是资本主义的自然副产。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:41.50,English,,0,0,0,,We live in a stage, we live in an age of late -stage capitalism.\N{\rChinese}我们处在一个阶段，处在晚期资本主义的时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.80,0:15:45.50,English,,0,0,0,,Is this clear to you guys?\N{\rChinese}你们听懂了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.00,0:15:47.66,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions before I move on\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.58,0:15:49.94,English,,0,0,0,,to the second theory?\N{\rChinese}接下来是第二个理论吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.14,0:15:58.10,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's move on to the second theory called elite overproduction.\N{\rChinese}好的，接下来是第二个理论——精英过剩。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.66,0:16:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,And this was proposed by a\N{\rChinese}这由一位名叫彼得·图尔奇恩的历史学家提出。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.20,0:16:10.40,English,,0,0,0,,historian named Peter Turchin. And\N{\rChinese}彼得·图尔奇恩花了几十年时间研究社会兴起的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.40,0:16:15.80,English,,0,0,0,,Peter Turchin spent decades looking at why societies rise\N{\rChinese}Peter Turchin spent decadeslooking at why societies rise
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.80,0:16:18.32,English,,0,0,0,,and fall. He looked at the Roman Empire.\N{\rChinese}他研究了罗马帝国的兴衰。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.58,0:16:19.92,English,,0,0,0,,He looked at the French Revolution.\N{\rChinese}他研究了法国大革命。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.72,0:16:22.76,English,,0,0,0,,He looked at many different examples.\N{\rChinese}他研究了许多不同的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.41,0:16:25.10,English,,0,0,0,,And what he believed is\N{\rChinese}而他所相信的是
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.61,0:16:27.42,English,,0,0,0,,societies fall,\N{\rChinese}社会会衰落、衰退、崩溃，因精英过剩的想法。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.80,0:16:30.60,English,,0,0,0,,decline, collapse, because of the idea of elite overproduction.\N{\rChinese}decline, collapse, because of the idea of elite overproduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.62,0:16:33.54,English,,0,0,0,,Meaning you have too many\N{\rChinese}意思是你有太多
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.54,0:16:38.92,English,,0,0,0,,powerful people competing for limited positions of power.\N{\rChinese}强势人物争夺有限的权力位置。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.40,0:16:42.56,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So to understand this,\N{\rChinese}好了？所以要理解这个，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.74,0:16:46.80,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to talk about another experiment called rat utopia.\N{\rChinese}我将谈谈另一个实验，叫做“老鼠乌托邦”。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.20,0:16:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,And\N{\rChinese}而且
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.20,0:16:51.88,English,,0,0,0,,rat utopia was a series of experiments\N{\rChinese}“老鼠乌托邦”是一系列实验。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.88,0:16:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,conducted by an American scientist named James B.\N{\rChinese}由美国科学家詹姆斯·B·卡尔霍恩主持的实验。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.74,0:17:00.60,English,,0,0,0,,Calhoun. And he said,\N{\rChinese}他还说，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.60,0:17:03.48,English,,0,0,0,,what's the difference between And what James Calhoun was trying to do in his\N{\rChinese}什么是……与詹姆斯·卡尔霍恩在他的实验中尝试做的事之间的区别
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:09.44,English,,0,0,0,,experiments was trying to figure out what living in a world of abundance\N{\rChinese}实验是想弄清在丰盛、富足与安定的世界里生活意味着什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.44,0:17:12.12,English,,0,0,0,,and wealth and security meant.\N{\rChinese}在第二次世界大战之后，…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.56,0:17:14.58,English,,0,0,0,,After World War II,\N{\rChinese}After World WarII,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.86,0:17:18.94,English,,0,0,0,,the world was divided between the United States and the Soviet Union.\N{\rChinese}世界被美国和苏联分割。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.14,0:17:21.28,English,,0,0,0,,It was the Cold War. But\N{\rChinese}那是冷战。但……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.28,0:17:25.42,English,,0,0,0,,it was also a time of increasing abundance due to technology\N{\rChinese}那也是技术带来丰盛的时代。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.42,0:17:27.22,English,,0,0,0,,and peace.\N{\rChinese}和和平。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.22,0:17:29.46,English,,0,0,0,,And the population was increasing.\N{\rChinese}人口在增长。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.82,0:17:35.54,English,,0,0,0,,So James Calhoun conducted these experiments to figure out what this meant for the world.\N{\rChinese}于是詹姆斯·卡尔霍恩开展这些实验，以弄清这对世界意味着什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.96,0:17:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,So what he did was this.\N{\rChinese}于是他做了这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:43.42,English,,0,0,0,,He had a room, okay, that was sealed off from the world.\N{\rChinese}他准备了一个房间，好的，那个房间与外界隔离。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.64,0:17:47.62,English,,0,0,0,,And in the room, he put in food\N{\rChinese}在房间里，他放了食物。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.62,0:17:51.80,English,,0,0,0,,and water and housing for a colony of rats.\N{\rChinese}和水以及为一群老鼠提供住所。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:54.16,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe like 10 rats at first.\N{\rChinese}一开始大约十只老鼠。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,But they quickly, um,\N{\rChinese}但它们很快，嗯，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.22,0:17:59.80,English,,0,0,0,,became 400, 500 rats.\N{\rChinese}变成400、500只老鼠。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.18,0:18:04.52,English,,0,0,0,,And at first, the rats were really happy.\N{\rChinese}起初，老鼠们非常开心。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.96,0:18:07.48,English,,0,0,0,,But no matter how Calhoun,\N{\rChinese}但无论Calhoun怎样，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.22,0:18:11.50,English,,0,0,0,,um, configured the experiment,\N{\rChinese}嗯，配置实验，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.36,0:18:17.16,English,,0,0,0,,ultimately, the rats always ended up killing each other.\N{\rChinese}最终，老鼠总是互相杀死。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.46,0:18:21.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So what he discovered is\N{\rChinese}好的？所以他发现的就是。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.96,0:18:24.94,English,,0,0,0,,if you live in a world of abundance and security,\N{\rChinese}如果你生活在丰裕与安全的世界里，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:29.62,English,,0,0,0,,the end result is, the rats always kill each other.\N{\rChinese}最终结果是，老鼠总是互相杀死。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.08,0:18:35.90,English,,0,0,0,,And he kept on doing this for 20 years.\N{\rChinese}他又继续做了二十年。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.12,0:18:37.58,English,,0,0,0,,And he could never, ever\N{\rChinese}他总是……
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.02,0:18:41.66,English,,0,0,0,,create a situation in which the rats lived peacefully.\N{\rChinese}创造一个老鼠能安然相处的局面。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.88,0:18:44.66,English,,0,0,0,,And he could never figure out why this was the case.\N{\rChinese}他也没能弄清楚原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.90,0:18:49.00,English,,0,0,0,,And even today, there's a huge debate as to why this is the case.\N{\rChinese}而且至今，关于此事的辩论仍然巨大。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.20,0:18:50.56,English,,0,0,0,,But he had a theory, okay?\N{\rChinese}但他有一个理论，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.82,0:18:52.08,English,,0,0,0,,And the theory is this.\N{\rChinese}这个理论是这样的。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:57.28,English,,0,0,0,,The rats were not competing for food.\N{\rChinese}老鼠们并不是在争食物。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.54,0:18:59.94,English,,0,0,0,,They were really competing for status.\N{\rChinese}它们真正争的是地位。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.10,0:19:04.86,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So,\N{\rChinese}好的，明白了。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.98,0:19:08.12,English,,0,0,0,,let's think about this, okay? In a state of nature,\N{\rChinese}先来想想这个，行吗？在自然状态下，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.68,0:19:13.90,English,,0,0,0,,in the real world, rats compete each other for mating rights,\N{\rChinese}在现实世界里，老鼠互相竞争交配权利，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.06,0:19:18.60,English,,0,0,0,,right? So, uh, you see a beautiful rat,\N{\rChinese}对吧？所以，你看到一只漂亮的老鼠，
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.14,0:19:21.62,English,,0,0,0,,and you, you fight over her, right?\N{\rChinese}你们也会为她争斗，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.94,0:19:26.74,English,,0,0,0,,The rat who wins out is now the alpha male.\N{\rChinese}赢得胜利的老鼠现在就是α雄。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.76,0:19:34.14,English,,0,0,0,,And the alpha male can have as many female companions as he wants.\N{\rChinese}α雄可以随心所欲地拥有任意多的雌伴。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.82,0:19:37.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And what do the other rats do?\N{\rChinese}好的？其他老鼠会怎么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.86,0:19:42.60,English,,0,0,0,,In nature, what will the other rats do?\N{\rChinese}在自然状态下，其他老鼠会怎样？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.88,0:19:48.00,English,,0,0,0,,Well, the other rats will probably run away, go somewhere else,\N{\rChinese}嗯，其他老鼠大概会跑开，去别处去。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.10,0:19:50.60,English,,0,0,0,,and find other female companions, right?\N{\rChinese}并且去找其他雌伴，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.74,0:19:52.58,English,,0,0,0,,Because everyone's trying to be the alpha male.\N{\rChinese}因为大家都想成为α雄。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.52,0:19:56.40,English,,0,0,0,,But in, what's the problem with James Calhoun's experiment?\N{\rChinese}但在这里，贾姆斯·卡尔霍恩实验有什么问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.52,0:20:00.76,English,,0,0,0,,Why do they fight each other?\N{\rChinese}它们为什么互相争斗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.60,0:20:04.80,English,,0,0,0,,There's no place for them to go.\N{\rChinese}它们没有去处可去。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.12,0:20:06.54,English,,0,0,0,,They're stuck where they are.\N{\rChinese}它们被困在原地。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.26,0:20:09.62,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? So,\N{\rChinese}你明白了吗？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.18,0:20:14.04,English,,0,0,0,,status is what we call a zero -sum game.\N{\rChinese}状态就是我们所说的零和游戏。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.88,0:20:18.40,English,,0,0,0,,I win, you lose.\N{\rChinese}我赢，你输。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.46,0:20:21.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There can only be one winner.\N{\rChinese}好的？只能有一个赢家。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.22,0:20:24.76,English,,0,0,0,,But, in nature,\N{\rChinese}但是，在自然界，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.98,0:20:27.88,English,,0,0,0,,if I win, then the other rats run away\N{\rChinese}如果我赢了，其他老鼠就会跑掉。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.88,0:20:31.44,English,,0,0,0,,and try to figure out, try to, try to build their own colony.\N{\rChinese}并尝试去弄清楚，尝试，尝试去建造自己的殖民。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.72,0:20:34.96,English,,0,0,0,,But in James Calhoun's experiment, there's no place for them to go.\N{\rChinese}但在詹姆斯·卡尔霍恩的实验里，他们没有去处。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:39.26,English,,0,0,0,,And so, all that happens is they keep on fighting each other until\N{\rChinese}于是，所有的事就是他们一直互相争斗。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.94,0:20:42.80,English,,0,0,0,,they, they die. Okay?\N{\rChinese}他们，他们死了。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.94,0:20:44.76,English,,0,0,0,,And that's the idea of elite overproduction.\N{\rChinese}这就是精英过度繁衍的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.14,0:20:47.28,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what Peter Turchin says.\N{\rChinese}这正是彼得·图尔奇所说的。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.74,0:20:52.64,English,,0,0,0,,The elite, the children of the elite, are always in the middle.\N{\rChinese}精英，精英的子嗣，始终在中间。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.64,0:20:55.34,English,,0,0,0,,Fighting for positions of power.\N{\rChinese}争夺权力位置。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.14,0:20:58.04,English,,0,0,0,,Not normal people, it's the children of the elite.\N{\rChinese}非普通人，乃精英之子嗣。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.44,0:21:00.76,English,,0,0,0,,But eventually, they have too many children\N{\rChinese}但最终，他们的子嗣太多了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.64,0:21:04.14,English,,0,0,0,,and there are not enough positions of power.\N{\rChinese}而且权力位置不够用
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.66,0:21:07.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Another, another way of saying this is that\N{\rChinese}好吧？换个说法就是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.66,0:21:12.06,English,,0,0,0,,in China today, there are too many graduates of Peking University,\N{\rChinese}在今天的中国，清华大学的毕业生太多了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.50,0:21:14.36,English,,0,0,0,,Beida, and Tsinghua University.\N{\rChinese}清华，没错？他们想当大老板。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.52,0:21:19.24,English,,0,0,0,,Tsinghua, right? They want to be the big boss.\N{\rChinese}清华，没错？他们想当大老板。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.90,0:21:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,They want to have the power.\N{\rChinese}他们想掌握权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:25.50,English,,0,0,0,,But there's too many of them. Okay?\N{\rChinese}但他们太多了，好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.94,0:21:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,There's no, and there's no place for them to go.\N{\rChinese}又没有，且他们也没有去处。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.58,0:21:29.94,English,,0,0,0,,And that leads to conflict in society.\N{\rChinese}这导致社会冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.78,0:21:35.06,English,,0,0,0,,And ultimately, what Peter Turchin has discovered is,\N{\rChinese}最终，彼得·图尔奇发现的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.68,0:21:37.24,English,,0,0,0,,if that's the case, then\N{\rChinese}如果是这样的话，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.24,0:21:41.58,English,,0,0,0,,elite overproduction will ultimately lead to either war or revolution.\N{\rChinese}精英过剩最终会导致战争或革命。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.52,0:21:44.10,English,,0,0,0,,It will lead to the collapse of society.\N{\rChinese}它将导致社会崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.32,0:21:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,And there's no way around this.\N{\rChinese}没有办法绕过此。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.64,0:21:48.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's Peter Turchin.\N{\rChinese}好的？那就是彼得·图尔奇。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.68,0:21:53.72,English,,0,0,0,,Now, I want to go to the third theory.\N{\rChinese}现在，我想进入第三个理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.42,0:21:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,And the third theory is the idea of a\N{\rChinese}第三个理论是……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.38,0:22:02.78,English,,0,0,0,,civilizational life cycle.\N{\rChinese}文化生命周期。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.72,0:22:07.48,English,,0,0,0,,And this is proposed by a German philosopher,\N{\rChinese}并且这由一位德国哲学家提出，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.40,0:22:10.92,English,,0,0,0,,scholar named Oswald Spangler.\N{\rChinese}名为奥斯瓦尔德·斯潘格尔。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.34,0:22:17.40,English,,0,0,0,,And what he argues is that\N{\rChinese}而他所论证的是
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.56,0:22:23.16,English,,0,0,0,,society, culture, civilization, it's no different from a person.\N{\rChinese}社会、文化、文明，跟个人没有区别。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.72,0:22:28.46,English,,0,0,0,,As a person, as a human being, we go through a life cycle.\N{\rChinese}作为个人，作为人类，我们经历人生周期。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.62,0:22:32.74,English,,0,0,0,,We are born, we grow up, we mature,\N{\rChinese}我们出生，成长，成熟，然后死亡。对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.56,0:22:36.50,English,,0,0,0,,then we die. Right?\N{\rChinese}而且没有办法绕过这一步。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.66,0:22:38.26,English,,0,0,0,,And there's no way around this.\N{\rChinese}And there's no way around this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.30,0:22:42.16,English,,0,0,0,,We all have limited life cycles.\N{\rChinese}我们都有有限的生命周期。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.70,0:22:45.02,English,,0,0,0,,You can live to 100.\N{\rChinese}你可以活到一百岁。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.16,0:22:48.14,English,,0,0,0,,You can live to 150. But eventually you'll die.\N{\rChinese}你可以活到一百五十岁。但最终你会死去。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.60,0:22:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,And what Oswald Spangler said, is that\N{\rChinese}而奥斯瓦尔德·斯潘格尔所说的，正是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.96,0:22:53.98,English,,0,0,0,,happens in society as well.\N{\rChinese}这同样在社会中发生着
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.08,0:22:56.48,English,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing anyone can do about this.\N{\rChinese}而且无论谁都无能为此做什么
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.72,0:23:00.44,English,,0,0,0,,So let's go over the life cycle for civilization.\N{\rChinese}那么我们来梳理一下文明的生命周期。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.82,0:23:04.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? In the beginning, you are in the village.\N{\rChinese}好的？一开始，你在村庄里。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.94,0:23:07.66,English,,0,0,0,,Then you move to the town.\N{\rChinese}然后你搬到城镇。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.48,0:23:09.94,English,,0,0,0,,Then you move to the city.\N{\rChinese}然后你搬到城镇。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.66,0:23:12.46,English,,0,0,0,,Then you develop the mega city.\N{\rChinese}然后你发展成大都市。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.30,0:23:18.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Not all civilizations will go through this cycle.\N{\rChinese}好？并非所有文明都经历这个循环。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.28,0:23:22.08,English,,0,0,0,,But the successful ones, will go through this cycle.\N{\rChinese}但成功的会经历这个循环。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.66,0:23:25.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You start off, so the Romans, right?\N{\rChinese}好？你先从罗马开始，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.50,0:23:29.30,English,,0,0,0,,The Qing Dynasty. You start off in a village.\N{\rChinese}好？先从村庄开始。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.90,0:23:33.30,English,,0,0,0,,Then, if you're successful in the village, you build a town.\N{\rChinese}然后，如果你在村庄成功，你就建城镇。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.72,0:23:35.80,English,,0,0,0,,Then, when you're in a town,\N{\rChinese}然后，当你在城镇时，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.40,0:23:40.30,English,,0,0,0,,and you're successful, you defeat other towns, and you build a city, and you become a mega city.\N{\rChinese}然后，你成功后，征服其他城镇，建成城市，成为大都市。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.56,0:23:44.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And what Oswald Spangler says is, at the height of the civilization,\N{\rChinese}好的？奥斯瓦尔德·斯潘格尔说，文明巅峰时，文明就该消亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.40,0:23:47.68,English,,0,0,0,,the civilization must now die.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是，】
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.18,0:23:50.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.12,0:23:52.54,English,,0,0,0,,let's go over the theory.\N{\rChinese}让我们来回顾一下理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.90,0:23:56.28,English,,0,0,0,,Well, in the village, life is pretty simple.\N{\rChinese}在村庄里，生活相当简单。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.50,0:23:58.76,English,,0,0,0,,People work hard.\N{\rChinese}人们勤劳工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.00,0:24:03.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They are united.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们团结在一起。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.34,0:24:04.58,English,,0,0,0,,They have a collective mentality.\N{\rChinese}他们拥有集体思维。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.16,0:24:09.84,English,,0,0,0,,Everyone's helping each other. And also, what's really important is,\N{\rChinese}大家互相帮助。更重要的是……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.36,0:24:13.00,English,,0,0,0,,lots of babies, right?\N{\rChinese}很多小宝宝，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.80,0:24:17.66,English,,0,0,0,,It's very common for, you know,\N{\rChinese}很常见，嗯，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.60,0:24:22.18,English,,0,0,0,,mothers to give birth to 10,\N{\rChinese}母亲们会生十个孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.24,0:24:24.46,English,,0,0,0,,11 kids in a village.\N{\rChinese}村里有11个孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.72,0:24:28.90,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And the reason why is, kids are free labor.\N{\rChinese}对吧？之所以如此，是因为孩子们是自由劳动力。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.76,0:24:33.44,English,,0,0,0,,So, you're incentivized to have as many children as possible.\N{\rChinese}于是你就会被激励尽可能多生孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.38,0:24:37.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, this is the framework of a village.\N{\rChinese}好的。这样就是村落的框架。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.90,0:24:43.34,English,,0,0,0,,But, as you go up the civilization ladder,\N{\rChinese}但当你攀升文明阶梯时，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.56,0:24:45.56,English,,0,0,0,,as you mature as a civilization,\N{\rChinese}随着文明的成熟，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.12,0:24:47.54,English,,0,0,0,,what happens is,\N{\rChinese}发生的事是，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.12,0:24:50.20,English,,0,0,0,,you have increased abstraction.\N{\rChinese}你有了更高层的抽象。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.08,0:24:56.34,English,,0,0,0,,Abstraction is just a fancy word for, you're removed from reality.\N{\rChinese}抽象只是个花哨词，意思是你已脱离现实。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.40,0:25:01.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, when you're in a village, you understand everything, right?\N{\rChinese}好的？那么，当你在村里时，你就能理解一切，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.26,0:25:03.68,English,,0,0,0,,You understand, oh, the food that\N{\rChinese}你明白，哦，吃的食物是
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.68,0:25:06.96,English,,0,0,0,,I eat comes from the seeds I implant.\N{\rChinese}我种下的种子发出的。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.88,0:25:10.58,English,,0,0,0,,Right? But when you're in a city, guess what?\N{\rChinese}对吧？但你在城里，猜猜是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.48,0:25:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,That those drinks you're drinking, you have no idea where it comes from.\N{\rChinese}你喝的那杯饮料，你根本不知道它来自哪儿。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.18,0:25:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,Right? The food you're eating, you have no idea where it comes from.\N{\rChinese}你吃的那顿饭，你根本不知道它来自哪儿。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.66,0:25:19.40,English,,0,0,0,,It's all abstract to you.\N{\rChinese}一切都抽象化了。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.44,0:25:20.80,English,,0,0,0,,It's all removed from reality.\N{\rChinese}一切都脱离了现实。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.00,0:25:25.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Um, so,\N{\rChinese}好吧？呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.24,0:25:30.40,English,,0,0,0,,in the village, people are engaged in working hard\N{\rChinese}在村里，人们勤劳工作
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.40,0:25:32.92,English,,0,0,0,,and in helping each other.\N{\rChinese}并互相帮助。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.20,0:25:37.82,English,,0,0,0,,But as you move up, people become much more individualistic.\N{\rChinese}但随着层级上升，人们变得更具个人性。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.34,0:25:42.54,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You're concerned about your own personal pleasure.\N{\rChinese}对吧？你在乎自己的个人乐趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.80,0:25:44.46,English,,0,0,0,,You're concerned about what,\N{\rChinese}你在乎什么，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.52,0:25:48.08,English,,0,0,0,,how do I derive benefit from this?\N{\rChinese}我怎样从中获得收益？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.98,0:25:52.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, another way of saying this is, in a village,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，另一种说法是，在一个村庄里
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.60,0:25:56.10,English,,0,0,0,,what keeps people together are emotions and tradition\N{\rChinese}情感与传统以及关系把人们聚在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.02,0:25:58.28,English,,0,0,0,,and relationships.\N{\rChinese}情感、传统与关系
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.84,0:26:02.62,English,,0,0,0,,But when you move to a megacity, what is it that holds people together?\N{\rChinese}但当你搬到大都市时，是什么把人们聚在一起？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.94,0:26:05.66,English,,0,0,0,,It's money. Right?\N{\rChinese}就是钱。对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.86,0:26:07.88,English,,0,0,0,,Money is the greatest abstraction.\N{\rChinese}钱是最大的抽象。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.18,0:26:12.42,English,,0,0,0,,The problem with money is that\N{\rChinese}钱的问题在于
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.58,0:26:16.98,English,,0,0,0,,it means we don't have to ever change.\N{\rChinese}它意味着我们不必再改变。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.98,0:26:19.92,English,,0,0,0,,We trust each other. In a village,\N{\rChinese}我们彼此信任。在村里，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.06,0:26:22.62,English,,0,0,0,,if you get sick, everyone comes and helps you.\N{\rChinese}如果你生病，大家都会来帮你。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.80,0:26:25.70,English,,0,0,0,,Right? But in the city, if you get sick,\N{\rChinese}对吧？但在城市里，如果你生病，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.76,0:26:28.72,English,,0,0,0,,you go to the hospital and pay the doctor.\N{\rChinese}你去医院付医生费。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.96,0:26:30.46,English,,0,0,0,,Your neighbors don't have to care.\N{\rChinese}你的邻居不必关心。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.64,0:26:32.18,English,,0,0,0,,Your family doesn't have to help you.\N{\rChinese}家人不必帮你。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.38,0:26:34.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So you become individualized.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是你变得个体化。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.80,0:26:36.82,English,,0,0,0,,You become atomized.\N{\rChinese}你变得原子化。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.66,0:26:42.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And in the megacity,\N{\rChinese}好吧？而在大都市，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.44,0:26:44.00,English,,0,0,0,,what happens is, because\N{\rChinese}发生的事是，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.00,0:26:48.72,English,,0,0,0,,you are concerned only about your own individual pleasure,\N{\rChinese}只关心自己的个人快乐
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.02,0:26:50.88,English,,0,0,0,,you don't work hard anymore.\N{\rChinese}你不再努力工作了。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.20,0:26:53.20,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, what you want to do is,\N{\rChinese}实际上，你想做的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.54,0:26:56.90,English,,0,0,0,,you want immigrants to work for you.\N{\rChinese}你想让移民为你工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.74,0:27:03.02,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You no longer care about other people.\N{\rChinese}对吧？你不再关心别人了。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.14,0:27:06.02,English,,0,0,0,,All you care about is yourself. And guess what, guys?\N{\rChinese}你只关心自己。你猜怎么了，伙计们？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.22,0:27:07.84,English,,0,0,0,,You don't want to have any children.\N{\rChinese}你不想要孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.38,0:27:11.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好吧？还有
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.14,0:27:15.08,English,,0,0,0,,that's why the megacity represents the death of civilization.\N{\rChinese}这就是为什么大都市代表文明的衰亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.38,0:27:17.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And what is Beijing?\N{\rChinese}好吧？那北京是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.36,0:27:18.56,English,,0,0,0,,What is Shanghai?\N{\rChinese}上海是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.80,0:27:20.08,English,,0,0,0,,What is Washington DC?\N{\rChinese}华盛顿特区是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.30,0:27:22.28,English,,0,0,0,,What is New York? What is Paris?\N{\rChinese}纽约是什么？巴黎又是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.42,0:27:24.28,English,,0,0,0,,What is London? They're all megacities.\N{\rChinese}伦敦是什么？它们都是大都市。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.66,0:27:26.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好吧？还有
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.96,0:27:30.78,English,,0,0,0,,that's why we have these trends.\N{\rChinese}这就是我们有这些趋势的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.14,0:27:33.92,English,,0,0,0,,And what Oswald Spengler says is,\N{\rChinese}而奥斯瓦尔德·斯彭格勒所说的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.04,0:27:37.12,English,,0,0,0,,there's nothing anyone can do about this.\N{\rChinese}这件事谁也做不了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.22,0:27:39.70,English,,0,0,0,,It is a natural life cycle.\N{\rChinese}它是自然的生命周期。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.40,0:27:43.12,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So these are the three major theories.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以这就是三大理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.24,0:27:45.26,English,,0,0,0,,I want you guys to remember.\N{\rChinese}我想让你们记住。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.26,0:27:48.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Sorry.\N{\rChinese}好的？抱歉。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.58,0:27:51.54,English,,0,0,0,,Can you give the microphone? Yeah.\N{\rChinese}你能递麦吗？好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.60,0:27:53.46,English,,0,0,0,,Can you just speak in the front row? Audience member 1 But\N{\rChinese}你能在前排说吗？观众1
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.46,0:27:57.58,English,,0,0,0,,what if there is a universal target that\N{\rChinese}如果有一个统一目标，迫使大家一起合作呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.44,0:28:00.72,English,,0,0,0,,forces everyone needs to work together?\N{\rChinese}你知道，这样会不会成功吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.54,0:28:05.94,English,,0,0,0,,You know, will that work out to like,\N{\rChinese}You know, will that work out to like,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.42,0:28:12.62,English,,0,0,0,,everyone just put down all of these problems\N{\rChinese}大家把这些问题都放下来
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.62,0:28:15.24,English,,0,0,0,,and figure out that, like,\N{\rChinese}然后想想，像是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.98,0:28:18.34,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay, I understand.\N{\rChinese}好的，我懂了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.54,0:28:20.46,English,,0,0,0,,That is a great question, okay?\N{\rChinese}那是个很好的问题，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.60,0:28:23.54,English,,0,0,0,,So the question, to rephrase it, okay, is,\N{\rChinese}所以问题，重新表述一下，好的，是，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.86,0:28:26.34,English,,0,0,0,,yeah, but what if there's an external threat,\N{\rChinese}是的，但如果有外部威胁，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.86,0:28:28.36,English,,0,0,0,,okay? An external threat.\N{\rChinese}好的？外部威胁。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.36,0:28:30.14,English,,0,0,0,,If there's an external threat,\N{\rChinese}如果有外部威胁，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.48,0:28:35.46,English,,0,0,0,,then\N{\rChinese}那么
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.46,0:28:38.44,English,,0,0,0,,surely this system,\N{\rChinese}当然这个系统，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.62,0:28:42.58,English,,0,0,0,,this life cycle, can be extended, right?\N{\rChinese}这个生命周期，可以延伸，吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.66,0:28:45.72,English,,0,0,0,,And external threats are examples of, hey, let's say there's an alien invasion.\N{\rChinese}而外部威胁是例子，嘿，假设有外星侵袭。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.80,0:28:51.28,English,,0,0,0,,Let's just say China's being attacked by the United States,\N{\rChinese}假设中国被美国攻击，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.38,0:28:53.02,English,,0,0,0,,right?\N{\rChinese}对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.74,0:28:58.34,English,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, the answer is no.\N{\rChinese}不幸的是，答案是没有。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.36,0:29:01.68,English,,0,0,0,,It does not matter. Because\N{\rChinese}这不重要。因为
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.68,0:29:04.36,English,,0,0,0,,once you've reached the point of a megacity,\N{\rChinese}一旦你们达到了大都市的阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.68,0:29:07.82,English,,0,0,0,,first of all, you're so selfish,\N{\rChinese}首先，你很自私，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.10,0:29:11.36,English,,0,0,0,,you're self -absorbed, you are not aware of external threats.\N{\rChinese}你自我沉浸，未察外部威胁。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.36,0:29:17.78,English,,0,0,0,,The other issue is you're no longer capable of working together\N{\rChinese}另一个问题是你们不再能一起工作
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.78,0:29:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,because you don't trust each other, okay?\N{\rChinese}因为你们互不信任，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.12,0:29:26.26,English,,0,0,0,,So the external threats factor doesn't really matter.\N{\rChinese}外部威胁因素其实不重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.34,0:29:28.10,English,,0,0,0,,But that's a great question. Thank you for asking, okay?\N{\rChinese}这确实是个好问题。谢谢你的提问，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.36,0:29:32.72,English,,0,0,0,,Yes, in theory, oh my God, if aliens come, then humans would unite.\N{\rChinese}是的，理论上，哦我的天啊，如果外星人来了，人类就会团结。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.92,0:29:34.18,English,,0,0,0,,No, that's not what would happen, okay?\N{\rChinese}不，那不是会发生的事，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.08,0:29:41.02,English,,0,0,0,,What would happen is certain factions of humans would try to align the aliens to conquer everyone else.\N{\rChinese}什么会发生的是，某些人类派别会试图把外星人拉拢来征服其余人。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.52,0:29:44.88,English,,0,0,0,,All right? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.24,0:29:48.34,English,,0,0,0,,So having gone through these three theories,\N{\rChinese}于是我把这三种理论都梳理完后，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.56,0:29:53.60,English,,0,0,0,,what I'm going to do is combine them together to create a comprehensive,\N{\rChinese}接下来我要把它们合并起来，形成一个完整的，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.06,0:29:58.14,English,,0,0,0,,holistic, broad theory.\N{\rChinese}整体的、宽广的理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.36,0:30:01.30,English,,0,0,0,,Of why societies rise and fall.\N{\rChinese}关于社会兴衰的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.94,0:30:03.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.98,0:30:08.96,English,,0,0,0,,And the problem with theories is they are simplistic\N{\rChinese}理论的难点在于它们过于简化。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.96,0:30:12.10,English,,0,0,0,,and inaccurate and imprecise.\N{\rChinese}并且不准确且不精确。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.28,0:30:16.78,English,,0,0,0,,So I'm, so I warn you that this theory has limitations.\N{\rChinese}于是我，先说这理论有局限。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.44,0:30:19.78,English,,0,0,0,,But for our purposes,\N{\rChinese}但对我们而言，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.90,0:30:23.52,English,,0,0,0,,what we want to do is have a working framework.\N{\rChinese}我们要做的事是有一个可用的框架。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.82,0:30:28.34,English,,0,0,0,,And then when we apply this framework to concrete examples, we can better rethink it.\N{\rChinese}然后把这个框架套到具体例子上，我们就能更好地重新思考它。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.36,0:30:30.02,English,,0,0,0,,refine this framework, okay?\N{\rChinese}再把框架细化一下，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.24,0:30:33.84,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, so I warn you that this framework, there are a lot of problems with it,\N{\rChinese}好的，我先说这个框架有不少问题，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.96,0:30:39.60,English,,0,0,0,,but it is a useful tool for us to analyze society in the past,\N{\rChinese}但它是我们分析过去社会的有用工具，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.84,0:30:41.24,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Alright, so\N{\rChinese}好的，先说吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.24,0:30:44.66,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to make generalizations about how society is structured.\N{\rChinese}我将对社会结构作出概括。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.24,0:30:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,So, at the core of society,\N{\rChinese}于是，社会的核心是……
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.42,0:30:49.92,English,,0,0,0,,the very powerful people,\N{\rChinese}最有权势的人们
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.78,0:30:53.94,English,,0,0,0,,these are certain families, okay?\N{\rChinese}这些是某些家族，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.06,0:30:57.00,English,,0,0,0,,These are the founding families of this nation.\N{\rChinese}这些是这个民族的创始家族。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.36,0:31:01.40,English,,0,0,0,,And there's not that many of them, maybe 10, maybe 100, but at most 100.\N{\rChinese}并且并不多，或许十家，或许百家，最多百家。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.98,0:31:06.62,English,,0,0,0,,So, if you go back to the Roman Empire, and the Roman Empire\N{\rChinese}于是，如果你回到罗马帝国，罗马帝国……
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.56,0:31:11.28,English,,0,0,0,,controlled most of Europe, as well as Anatolia,\N{\rChinese}它统治了欧洲大部分地区，也包括安那托利亚、埃及，面积很大，但实际上只有大约200个家族。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.48,0:31:15.92,English,,0,0,0,,Egypt, it was a huge area, but really, there were only about 200 families\N{\rChinese}Egypt, it was a huge area, but really, there were only about 200 families
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.58,0:31:18.34,English,,0,0,0,,that controlled the Roman Empire, okay?\N{\rChinese}那统治罗马帝国，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.06,0:31:22.50,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, so, how these families express power,\N{\rChinese}好吧，那么，这些家族如何展现权力，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.82,0:31:25.76,English,,0,0,0,,how they control power in society is through\N{\rChinese}他们如何通过社会掌控权力是通过
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.78,0:31:30.12,English,,0,0,0,,three mechanisms. Three pillars of power.\N{\rChinese}三种机制。权力的三大支柱。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.36,0:31:33.54,English,,0,0,0,,And these three pillars are finance.\N{\rChinese}这三大支柱是财政。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.00,0:31:39.80,English,,0,0,0,,Finance, we talked about last class, it's just central banking.\N{\rChinese}财政，我们上节课说过，它就是中央银行。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.30,0:31:44.12,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? Second pillar is religion.\N{\rChinese}好吧？第二支柱是宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.20,0:31:51.58,English,,0,0,0,,Religion is just what people believe, how to control what people believe.\N{\rChinese}宗教就是人们的信仰，如何掌控人们的信仰。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.98,0:31:56.38,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the religion of today is science and technology.\N{\rChinese}现在，今天的宗教就是科学与技术。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.78,0:32:00.38,English,,0,0,0,,Science and technology. And the third pillar is\N{\rChinese}科学与技术。第三个支柱是智力。或者说间谍。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.12,0:32:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,intelligence. Or spies.\N{\rChinese}好吧？现在，为了方便，...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.42,0:32:11.70,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? Now, for the purpose of,\N{\rChinese}Alright? Now, for the purpose of,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.74,0:32:15.70,English,,0,0,0,,to save time, I'm not going to go too deeply into intelligence\N{\rChinese}为了省时，我不打算深入探讨智力与宗教，但以后课会讲，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.70,0:32:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,and religion, but I will in future classes, okay?\N{\rChinese}我只要你记住，力量有三根支柱。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.00,0:32:21.62,English,,0,0,0,,I just need you to remember that there are three pillars of power\N{\rChinese}I just need you to remember thatthere are three pillars of power
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.28,0:32:25.98,English,,0,0,0,,at the core of society. Finance, intelligence, and religion.\N{\rChinese}在社会核心。财政、情报与宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.26,0:32:27.88,English,,0,0,0,,And it's their nexus,\N{\rChinese}而它们的纽带，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.36,0:32:31.32,English,,0,0,0,,their combination that\N{\rChinese}它们的组合
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.32,0:32:33.98,English,,0,0,0,,allows the elite to control everyone else.\N{\rChinese}让精英掌控其余众。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.36,0:32:38.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, from this nexus,\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是从这纽带，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.62,0:32:43.54,English,,0,0,0,,they will control all aspects of society,\N{\rChinese}他们将统御社会各个层面。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.04,0:32:45.26,English,,0,0,0,,including schools,\N{\rChinese}包括学校，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.36,0:32:50.24,English,,0,0,0,,including the military, including government,\N{\rChinese}包括军队，政府，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.70,0:32:57.30,English,,0,0,0,,including the media, including culture,\N{\rChinese}包括媒体，文化，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.40,0:33:01.10,English,,0,0,0,,including crime, the mafia.\N{\rChinese}包括犯罪、黑手党。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.42,0:33:03.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Every aspect of society that\N{\rChinese}好的？社会的每个方面，你能想象的，都在这股力量的掌控之中。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.62,0:33:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,you can imagine is being controlled in some respect by this nexus of power.\N{\rChinese}好的？社会的每个方面，你能想象的，都在这股力量的掌控之中。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.62,0:33:12.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Also you have like\N{\rChinese}好的？还有你会有像…
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.68,0:33:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,corporations, right? And\N{\rChinese}公司，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.64,0:33:20.84,English,,0,0,0,,then, at the outer edge, are the people.\N{\rChinese}然后，在外缘是人们。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.78,0:33:25.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The people because\N{\rChinese}好吧？人们因为
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.82,0:33:30.54,English,,0,0,0,,they're so massive, the massive people, they're the ones who generate wealth for society.\N{\rChinese}他们很大，巨大的人民，他们是为社会创造财富的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.90,0:33:33.96,English,,0,0,0,,So this system is designed to\N{\rChinese}于是这个系统就是这么设计的。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.82,0:33:38.82,English,,0,0,0,,create as much energy as possible for the people.\N{\rChinese}为人民创造尽可能多的能量。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.02,0:33:41.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Energy. Because\N{\rChinese}好吧？能量。因为
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.60,0:33:45.66,English,,0,0,0,,the harder the people work, the more wealth is generated in society.\N{\rChinese}人们工作越努力，社会产生的财富越多。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.80,0:33:51.40,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So, a metaphor that we can use is this.\N{\rChinese}好了？我们可以用的一个比喻是这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.64,0:33:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,Think of society as a corporation.\N{\rChinese}把社会想象成一家企业。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.90,0:33:55.68,English,,0,0,0,,The people are the workers, right?\N{\rChinese}人们就是工人，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.84,0:33:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,They're the ones who do the real work.\N{\rChinese}他们是实际工作的那一群人。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.76,0:34:02.72,English,,0,0,0,,The elite, these families, are the owners.\N{\rChinese}精英，这些家族，就是所有者。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.64,0:34:08.04,English,,0,0,0,,And these people in between, the middle class, are the managers.\N{\rChinese}而这中间的那一群人，即中产阶层，就是管理者。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.34,0:34:12.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So again, this is a very simple\N{\rChinese}好的？再说一次，这是一种很简单的比喻，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.18,0:34:19.78,English,,0,0,0,,metaphor, and\N{\rChinese}而且它并不完全准确，但对分析很有用。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.78,0:34:22.60,English,,0,0,0,,it's not accurate, but it's useful for analysis.\N{\rChinese}it's not accurate, but it's useful for analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.00,0:34:26.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, the families are the owners of the corporation,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，家族是公司的所有者，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.04,0:34:31.16,English,,0,0,0,,the people are the workers, the people in between, the managers are the managers.\N{\rChinese}人们是工人，夹在中间的则是管理者。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.58,0:34:33.32,English,,0,0,0,,And we call these people the middle class.\N{\rChinese}我们把这些人称为中产阶层。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.30,0:34:36.84,English,,0,0,0,,There have been other names for it in China before in history.\N{\rChinese}在中国历史上曾有其他称呼。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.92,0:34:38.58,English,,0,0,0,,We call them the scholar officials, right?\N{\rChinese}我们称他们为文官，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.44,0:34:45.38,English,,0,0,0,,Um, another name for them is something called the professional managerial class,\N{\rChinese}嗯，另一个称呼是专业管理阶层。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.60,0:34:50.14,English,,0,0,0,,PMC. Also, another name for them is the\N{\rChinese}PMC。另一个称呼是小资产阶层。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.18,0:34:53.46,English,,0,0,0,,petty bourgeoisie. Okay?\N{\rChinese}好？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.46,0:34:55.70,English,,0,0,0,,Again, you don't need to know these names.\N{\rChinese}再说一次，你不必记住这些名称。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.76,0:34:59.94,English,,0,0,0,,For the purpose of simplicity, we will just call them the middle class.\N{\rChinese}为简化起见，我们把它们称作中产阶层。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.76,0:35:02.50,English,,0,0,0,,Alright. Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}好的。这样说对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.86,0:35:05.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, having gone through the structure of society,\N{\rChinese}好了。既然已梳理完社会结构，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.90,0:35:10.36,English,,0,0,0,,let's talk about what happens when society rises and falls.\N{\rChinese}我们来聊聊社会兴衰时的变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.70,0:35:15.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? When it rises, the dynamic of these three groups, it's very interesting.\N{\rChinese}好的？当它兴起时，这三组的动态非常有趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.74,0:35:18.78,English,,0,0,0,,When it rises, the families who\N{\rChinese}当它兴起时，家庭…
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.78,0:35:22.10,English,,0,0,0,,own the nation are happy\N{\rChinese}拥有民族的人民很高兴
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.76,0:35:24.46,English,,0,0,0,,to let the manager\N{\rChinese}让经理来掌控社会
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.86,0:35:29.16,English,,0,0,0,,control society. And this is what we call democracy, right?\N{\rChinese}这就是我们所说的民主，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.18,0:35:34.22,English,,0,0,0,,And the managers are always providing feedback to the families\N{\rChinese}并且经理们总是向家庭反馈，并说我们应该更好地对待工人。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.22,0:35:36.18,English,,0,0,0,,and saying, we should treat workers better.\N{\rChinese}如果我们更好地对待工人，那么…
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.36,0:35:38.52,English,,0,0,0,,If we treat workers better, then\N{\rChinese}If we treat workers better, then
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.16,0:35:40.46,English,,0,0,0,,they will work harder.\N{\rChinese}他们会更努力工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.38,0:35:45.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And at this point, things are great.\N{\rChinese}好的？此时一切都很顺利。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.60,0:35:48.58,English,,0,0,0,,The people feel that they have a voice in the system,\N{\rChinese}人们觉得自己在体制中有发声的权利。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.82,0:35:51.18,English,,0,0,0,,they're making good money, everyone's really happy.\N{\rChinese}他们赚了不少钱，大家都很开心。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.48,0:35:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,But, what happens because of the\N{\rChinese}但是，因为什么而发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.66,0:36:00.34,English,,0,0,0,,elite overproduction is, these families produce\N{\rChinese}精英过度生产导致这些家庭产生。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:04.74,English,,0,0,0,,too many children who want pieces of power.\N{\rChinese}孩子太多，想分得一点权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.06,0:36:08.38,English,,0,0,0,,Basically, they want to spend money from the corporation.\N{\rChinese}基本上，他们想把公司钱花出去。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.90,0:36:11.00,English,,0,0,0,,And now the corporation is in trouble.\N{\rChinese}现在公司陷入困境。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.28,0:36:13.82,English,,0,0,0,,It's in debt. Okay?\N{\rChinese}它在债务中。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.02,0:36:16.12,English,,0,0,0,,So at this point, what happens is this.\N{\rChinese}于是此时，发生的事是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.68,0:36:20.68,English,,0,0,0,,You would think the managers would say to the families, listen guys,\N{\rChinese}你会想，经理们会对家族说，听着，伙计们，
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.06,0:36:22.32,English,,0,0,0,,we need\N{\rChinese}我们需要
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.86,0:36:25.66,English,,0,0,0,,to be more fair to the people.\N{\rChinese}更公平对待人民。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.26,0:36:29.46,English,,0,0,0,,But what really happens in reality is, the managers\N{\rChinese}但实际上发生的事是，经理们
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.24,0:36:31.82,English,,0,0,0,,exploit the people.\N{\rChinese}利用人民。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.42,0:36:34.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The managers will now deceive.\N{\rChinese}好的？经理们现在会欺骗。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.32,0:36:39.20,English,,0,0,0,,They will lie to the people, they will commit fraud, they will exploit the people.\N{\rChinese}他们会对人民说谎，做欺诈，利用人民。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.56,0:36:41.96,English,,0,0,0,,Why? The reason why is this.\N{\rChinese}为什么？原因就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.66,0:36:46.18,English,,0,0,0,,What the managers really do is something called, um,\N{\rChinese}经理们真正做的事叫做，呃，……
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.70,0:36:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,rant seeking\N{\rChinese}发狂寻求
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.04,0:36:57.58,English,,0,0,0,,behavior. Okay?\N{\rChinese}行为。好的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.84,0:37:00.44,English,,0,0,0,,Ranting seeking behavior just means they have a certain power\N{\rChinese}发狂寻求行为只是指他们拥有某种力量
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.44,0:37:03.64,English,,0,0,0,,that they want to exploit in order to extract\N{\rChinese}他们想利用这种力量来提取
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.40,0:37:06.00,English,,0,0,0,,wealth from other people.\N{\rChinese}来自他人的财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.22,0:37:10.38,English,,0,0,0,,So for example, the most classic example is, you own an apartment in Beijing, right?\N{\rChinese}比如说，最经典的例子是，你在北京拥有一套公寓，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.52,0:37:14.44,English,,0,0,0,,So you rent it out to someone who needs to live in Beijing, and you collect rent.\N{\rChinese}你把它租给需要住在北京的人，然后收租金。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.16,0:37:19.14,English,,0,0,0,,Well, this is true for, um, a lot of people.\N{\rChinese}好吧，这点对很多人都成立。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.32,0:37:21.84,English,,0,0,0,,So, if you are a lawyer,\N{\rChinese}所以，如果你是律师，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.10,0:37:23.82,English,,0,0,0,,you collect rent because\N{\rChinese}你收租金因为
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.82,0:37:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,only you can work in the court system.\N{\rChinese}只有你能在法院系统工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.08,0:37:32.42,English,,0,0,0,,So if you want to sue someone, or if you want, if you have a contract dispute, you have to go to a lawyer, okay?\N{\rChinese}所以如果你想起诉某人，或者你有合同争议，你得去找律师，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.52,0:37:35.64,English,,0,0,0,,The lawyer is collecting rent. And that's what the middle class,\N{\rChinese}律师在收租金。那就是中产阶层的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.94,0:37:37.50,English,,0,0,0,,the professional managerial class do.\N{\rChinese}专业管理阶层所做的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.62,0:37:39.30,English,,0,0,0,,They are rent seekers.\N{\rChinese}他们是租金寻求者。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.64,0:37:44.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the way we're saying this is, guys,\N{\rChinese}好了？我们这么说吧，伙计们。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.48,0:37:46.74,English,,0,0,0,,if you go to a company,\N{\rChinese}如果你去公司，你知道工人干啥，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.48,0:37:48.78,English,,0,0,0,,you know what the workers do, right?\N{\rChinese}你知道经理干啥吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.44,0:37:50.68,English,,0,0,0,,You know what the managers do?\N{\rChinese}你知道经理干啥吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.44,0:37:54.02,English,,0,0,0,,They really don't do that much. Okay?\N{\rChinese}他们真的没干那么多。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.14,0:37:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,And this is true for the middle class.\N{\rChinese}这对中产阶层也一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.64,0:38:00.24,English,,0,0,0,,Like, um,\N{\rChinese}呃，像是……
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.24,0:38:03.36,English,,0,0,0,,the managers, the middle class, live very nice lives.\N{\rChinese}经理们、中产阶层过着非常舒适的生活。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.84,0:38:06.38,English,,0,0,0,,And so, when the company's in trouble,\N{\rChinese}于是，当公司陷入困境时，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.60,0:38:11.36,English,,0,0,0,,managers are like, well, I have a very nice life, I have a very nice job, but I don't really do anything,\N{\rChinese}经理们会说：好吧，我过得很不错，工作也很轻松，但我并没有真正干活。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.16,0:38:13.66,English,,0,0,0,,so I'll probably be the first to get fired.\N{\rChinese}于是我大概会是第一个被解雇的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.04,0:38:15.94,English,,0,0,0,,So they have to show their worth.\N{\rChinese}于是他们得证明自己的价值。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.14,0:38:19.00,English,,0,0,0,,They have to prove their worth, and therefore, they exploit the workers.\N{\rChinese}他们得证明自己的价值，于是才会去剥削工人。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.80,0:38:24.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Do you understand? They push the workers harder to generate more wealth.\N{\rChinese}好的？你明白了吗？他们更用工人来创造更多财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.38,0:38:29.08,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So, in the decline phase,\N{\rChinese}对吧？所以，在衰退阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.42,0:38:31.86,English,,0,0,0,,this is not really a problem.\N{\rChinese}这其实不算问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.18,0:38:33.98,English,,0,0,0,,But what happens over time is,\N{\rChinese}但随着时间推移，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.56,0:38:36.34,English,,0,0,0,,the conflict within\N{\rChinese}精英内部的冲突愈演愈烈。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.86,0:38:38.78,English,,0,0,0,,the elite gets worse and worse.\N{\rChinese}the elite gets worse and worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.94,0:38:40.18,English,,0,0,0,,Elite overproduction.\N{\rChinese}精英过剩产量。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.42,0:38:43.34,English,,0,0,0,,And what will eventually happen is, they will form into factions\N{\rChinese}随后会形成各派，互相争夺权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.34,0:38:46.04,English,,0,0,0,,that compete against each other for power.\N{\rChinese}各派相互竞争，争夺权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.06,0:38:50.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And when\N{\rChinese}好的？然后
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.18,0:38:54.42,English,,0,0,0,,that happens, then society becomes aligned into\N{\rChinese}那时，社会就会分化成各派。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.86,0:38:57.70,English,,0,0,0,,factions. The factions will bring in certain elements of the middle class,\N{\rChinese}各派会把中产阶层的某些成员纳入其中。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.88,0:39:00.16,English,,0,0,0,,which will then bring in certain elements of the people.\N{\rChinese}随后会把部分人群纳入其中。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.90,0:39:03.90,English,,0,0,0,,And now,\N{\rChinese}现在，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.72,0:39:09.26,English,,0,0,0,,what happens is civil war or revolution.\N{\rChinese}随后发生的是内战或革命。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.06,0:39:12.18,English,,0,0,0,,And this marks the collapse of society.\N{\rChinese}这标志着社会的崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.00,0:39:15.24,English,,0,0,0,,What's really important for us to remember is,\N{\rChinese}我们要记住的关键是，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.50,0:39:20.28,English,,0,0,0,,this is a natural cycle, and no amount of external threat\N{\rChinese}这是一条自然循环，外部威胁无论多少都如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.86,0:39:22.18,English,,0,0,0,,will change that\N{\rChinese}它会改变那种格局。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.86,0:39:24.60,English,,0,0,0,,dynamic. Why? Because\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.86,0:39:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,it's very common for these factions to align with\N{\rChinese}这些派系很常与……
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.40,0:39:33.96,English,,0,0,0,,mercenaries. Okay?\N{\rChinese}雇佣兵。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.74,0:39:37.88,English,,0,0,0,,So, there's foreign invasions, not because\N{\rChinese}于是，出现外部入侵，并非因为……
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.88,0:39:42.20,English,,0,0,0,,some guy overseas is like, oh, this society is unstable, I'll come and invade.\N{\rChinese}某个海外人说：‘这社会不稳，我来入侵。’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.42,0:39:46.28,English,,0,0,0,,What happens often is, a certain faction invites mercenaries\N{\rChinese}某个派系常常邀请雇佣兵
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.80,0:39:48.50,English,,0,0,0,,into the nation\N{\rChinese}进入该民族国家
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.36,0:39:50.72,English,,0,0,0,,as part of the power struggle.\N{\rChinese}作为权力争斗的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.82,0:39:54.78,English,,0,0,0,,And then the mercenaries realize, you know what, we can stick this for ourselves.\N{\rChinese}于是雇佣兵们意识到，咱们可以把这件事留给自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.80,0:40:00.84,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So, when\N{\rChinese}好了？那时，……
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.84,0:40:04.04,English,,0,0,0,,you reach the collapse phase, the society is much too insular,\N{\rChinese}当你们进入崩溃阶段，社会就已经太内向了。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.96,0:40:07.94,English,,0,0,0,,much too wrapped with infighting to care about external threats.\N{\rChinese}已然已被内战缠绕，才会关心外部威胁。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.20,0:40:11.66,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why if there's an alien invasion, it really wouldn't change anything.\N{\rChinese}正因如此，若有外来入侵，实则不改其形。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.00,0:40:15.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Alright?\N{\rChinese}好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.02,0:40:20.26,English,,0,0,0,,Is this clear to you guys? So again, this is the model we're working with\N{\rChinese}这对你们来说清楚吗？所以再次说明，这是我们用来解释社会兴衰的模型。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.86,0:40:24.06,English,,0,0,0,,to explain the rise and fall of societies.\N{\rChinese}首先，在这个体系里，…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.38,0:40:28.32,English,,0,0,0,,At first, in this system,\N{\rChinese}At first, in this system,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.52,0:40:31.76,English,,0,0,0,,the elite families are willing to let the major class\N{\rChinese}精英家族愿意让主要阶级…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.10,0:40:35.68,English,,0,0,0,,incentivize and motivate the workers to do their best.\N{\rChinese}激励并激发工人发挥最佳表现。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.10,0:40:38.96,English,,0,0,0,,And you do that through democracy, through openness,\N{\rChinese}并且你通过民主、通过开放来实现。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.22,0:40:42.28,English,,0,0,0,,through meritocracy, through innovation.\N{\rChinese}通过才干制、通过创新。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.98,0:40:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,But over time, as these elite families have more\N{\rChinese}但随着时间推移，随着这些精英家族拥有更多
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.96,0:40:49.62,English,,0,0,0,,and more children, and these children are engaged in ransom behavior,\N{\rChinese}以及更多孩子，这些孩子从事赎金行为，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.06,0:40:51.98,English,,0,0,0,,they basically want to steal profits from the corporation,\N{\rChinese}他们基本想从公司偷取利润。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.70,0:40:54.84,English,,0,0,0,,the corporation runs into trouble, and then\N{\rChinese}公司出现麻烦，随后管理层被迫用力压人，导致更大冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.86,0:40:59.64,English,,0,0,0,,managers are forced to coerce the people, which leads to greater conflict.\N{\rChinese}管理层被迫用力压人，导致更大冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.26,0:41:03.30,English,,0,0,0,,And eventually, over time, the collapse happens when\N{\rChinese}最终，随着时间推移，崩溃发生在…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.30,0:41:07.56,English,,0,0,0,,society breaks up into different factions, which leads to civil war, or revolution,\N{\rChinese}社会分裂成不同派系，导致内战或革命。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.94,0:41:10.88,English,,0,0,0,,or war. Okay.\N{\rChinese}或者战争。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.18,0:41:12.58,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the model we're working with.\N{\rChinese}所以这就是我们正在使用的模型。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.92,0:41:16.42,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, any questions? Are you guys clear about this?\N{\rChinese}好的，大家有问题吗？你们对这点明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.70,0:41:23.20,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah? What if they just like,\N{\rChinese}嗯？他们只是……
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.24,0:41:25.16,English,,0,0,0,,don't have that much children?\N{\rChinese}没那么多孩子吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.90,0:41:28.48,English,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, what's the question?\N{\rChinese}请问，问题是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.78,0:41:33.24,English,,0,0,0,,Like, what if the family, the elite families don't have that much children?\N{\rChinese}比如说，家族，精英家族没那么多孩子吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.90,0:41:35.46,English,,0,0,0,,Will this model still work?\N{\rChinese}这个模型还可行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.76,0:41:38.10,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a great question. Okay.\N{\rChinese}哦，这是个好问题。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.64,0:41:42.32,English,,0,0,0,,So, what if families don't have that many children?\N{\rChinese}那么，如果家族没有那么多孩子呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.66,0:41:44.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's a really interesting question.\N{\rChinese}好的，真是个有趣的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.76,0:41:49.22,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer is, these families first and foremost, want to have as many children as possible.\N{\rChinese}答案是，这些家族首先想尽可能多地生孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.84,0:41:51.72,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Because how do you pass on your power?\N{\rChinese}对吧？因为怎样才能把权力传给下一代？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.00,0:41:54.94,English,,0,0,0,,... So,\N{\rChinese}...所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.94,0:41:59.52,English,,0,0,0,,maybe the middle class don't want to have that many\N{\rChinese}也许中产阶层不想生那么多孩子，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.16,0:42:02.88,English,,0,0,0,,children, but the elite will have a lot of children.\N{\rChinese}而精英阶层则会生很多孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.06,0:42:05.88,English,,0,0,0,,Because they need to be able to pass on their power and\N{\rChinese}因为他们需要能够把权力传给下一代并且……
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.88,0:42:08.16,English,,0,0,0,,privilege to their children.\N{\rChinese}……并把特权传给他们的孩子们。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.82,0:42:12.80,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, the elite is first and foremost concerned\N{\rChinese}事实上，精英阶层首先关心……
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.42,0:42:15.90,English,,0,0,0,,with passing on their privilege to the next generation.\N{\rChinese}传给下一代的特权。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.52,0:42:20.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's why these elite families expand so fast.\N{\rChinese}于是，这些精英家族扩张得如此迅速。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.06,0:42:23.42,English,,0,0,0,,And also, who wants to marry into elite families?\N{\rChinese}谁想嫁进精英家族呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.86,0:42:26.96,English,,0,0,0,,Who wants to marry into them? Everyone.\N{\rChinese}谁想嫁进他们？人人都想。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.20,0:42:30.70,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? And they have to\N{\rChinese}好吧？他们还得
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.70,0:42:35.24,English,,0,0,0,,marry into other families in order to maintain their power.\N{\rChinese}嫁进其他家族以维持权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.72,0:42:37.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.68,0:42:42.50,English,,0,0,0,,having children in a marriage is a way for the elite to maintain their power.\N{\rChinese}在婚姻中生子是精英维持权力的一种方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.20,0:42:46.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But that's a good question.\N{\rChinese}好吧？但这是个好问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.14,0:42:49.38,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions before I continue?\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.92,0:42:56.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, let us summarize what we've learned\N{\rChinese}好的。现在让我们总结到目前为止的内容并讨论。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.02,0:42:58.10,English,,0,0,0,,so far and discuss\N{\rChinese}so far and discuss
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.68,0:42:59.90,English,,0,0,0,,what is it\N{\rChinese}它是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.62,0:43:04.64,English,,0,0,0,,that allows societies to rise\N{\rChinese}它是什么让社会得以兴起
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.64,0:43:06.82,English,,0,0,0,,and fall. So, we'll look at three phases.\N{\rChinese}以及衰落
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.92,0:43:09.42,English,,0,0,0,,The rise, the decline,\N{\rChinese}兴起、衰落、
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.42,0:43:13.64,English,,0,0,0,,and the collapse.\N{\rChinese}以及崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.16,0:43:18.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, when I mean decline, I don't mean\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，我说衰落时，我指的是
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.78,0:43:21.22,English,,0,0,0,,like things are getting worse. I mean things aren't improving.\N{\rChinese}像事情变得更糟。我是说事情没有进步。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.42,0:43:23.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, rise is when things get better.\N{\rChinese}好？所以，兴起是事情变得更好。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.60,0:43:26.52,English,,0,0,0,,Decline is when things are stagnant or getting slightly worse.\N{\rChinese}衰落是事情停滞或略微变糟。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.70,0:43:29.70,English,,0,0,0,,Collapse is when society is about to fall apart.\N{\rChinese}崩溃是指社会即将崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.36,0:43:31.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.94,0:43:36.28,English,,0,0,0,,if you look at these three particular phases of society, there are different characteristics.\N{\rChinese}若你观察社会的这三个特定阶段，便可见其各异特征。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.56,0:43:41.62,English,,0,0,0,,When society rises, it is first and foremost open.\N{\rChinese}当社会兴起时，首先是开放的。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.84,0:43:45.88,English,,0,0,0,,Open just means that you have opportunities\N{\rChinese}开放就是指你在社会中拥有社会流动的机会。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.62,0:43:48.78,English,,0,0,0,,for social mobility in a society.\N{\rChinese}这些机会让你在社会中实现流动。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.42,0:43:51.70,English,,0,0,0,,If you're a poor person, you can make money.\N{\rChinese}如果你是个穷人，你也能赚钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.88,0:43:53.54,English,,0,0,0,,You can become wealthy.\N{\rChinese}你可以变得富有。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.74,0:43:55.16,English,,0,0,0,,Your talent is appreciated.\N{\rChinese}你的才华会被认可。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.42,0:43:57.08,English,,0,0,0,,It's a meritocracy. It's innovative.\N{\rChinese}它是才干制，创新型。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.90,0:43:59.30,English,,0,0,0,,If you criticize society,\N{\rChinese}若你批评社会，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.66,0:44:04.04,English,,0,0,0,,people are like, thank you for criticizing us because criticism makes us better people.\N{\rChinese}人们会说，感谢你批评我们，因为批评让我们更好。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.88,0:44:08.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There's open debate. Now, what's really interesting is\N{\rChinese}好的？有开放的辩论。现在，真正有趣的是
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.00,0:44:12.94,English,,0,0,0,,most young societies are open societies.\N{\rChinese}大多数年轻的社会都是开放的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.16,0:44:14.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, for example, in 1950s,\N{\rChinese}好的？比如说，在1950年代，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.10,0:44:19.42,English,,0,0,0,,America was a democracy, right?\N{\rChinese}美国是民主国家，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.98,0:44:22.42,English,,0,0,0,,China was communist.\N{\rChinese}中国是共产主义国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.60,0:44:25.04,English,,0,0,0,,But, this is really interesting.\N{\rChinese}这才是重点。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.04,0:44:27.68,English,,0,0,0,,In 1950s, they were both open societies.\N{\rChinese}1950年代，它们都是开放的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.96,0:44:31.14,English,,0,0,0,,You could criticize leaders. In fact, you were encouraged to criticize leaders.\N{\rChinese}你可以批评领导人。实际上，你被鼓励去批评领导人。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.96,0:44:34.22,English,,0,0,0,,China was as democratic back then\N{\rChinese}当时的中国也是民主的。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.84,0:44:37.50,English,,0,0,0,,as the United States. Okay?\N{\rChinese}就像美国一样。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.50,0:44:39.06,English,,0,0,0,,So, it's not about political systems.\N{\rChinese}所以，关键不在于政治制度。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.20,0:44:43.56,English,,0,0,0,,It's just about the what state you are in social development.\N{\rChinese}只是关于你所在的社会发展阶段。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.80,0:44:45.76,English,,0,0,0,,So, if you're young, you're going to be open.\N{\rChinese}所以，如果你年轻，你就会变得开放。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.88,0:44:47.66,English,,0,0,0,,You're going to be democratic. You're going to be meritocratic.\N{\rChinese}你会变得民主。你会变得才干主导。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.90,0:44:51.22,English,,0,0,0,,You want to learn, so you will listen to criticism.\N{\rChinese}你想学习，所以你会听取批评。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.40,0:44:54.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's the first great\N{\rChinese}好的？那是一个正在崛起的社会的第一个大特点。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.86,0:44:56.20,English,,0,0,0,,characteristic of a society on the rise.\N{\rChinese}它是开放性。但，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.34,0:44:59.54,English,,0,0,0,,It's openness. But,\N{\rChinese}It's openness. But,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.54,0:45:02.48,English,,0,0,0,,when you reach a decline phase, guess what?\N{\rChinese}当你进入衰落阶段时，猜猜会怎样？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.66,0:45:04.40,English,,0,0,0,,Society becomes bureaucratic.\N{\rChinese}社会变成官僚化。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.88,0:45:10.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Bureaucratic.\N{\rChinese}好吧？官僚化。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.58,0:45:13.22,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because, if we go back to this model,\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为，如果我们回到这个模型，[754]
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.28,0:45:16.36,English,,0,0,0,,as a company loses more and more money,\N{\rChinese}就像公司不断亏损，[755]
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.72,0:45:20.70,English,,0,0,0,,the managerial class is concerned with maintaining their jobs.\N{\rChinese}管理阶层只顾着保住自己的工作。[756]
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.20,0:45:23.42,English,,0,0,0,,So, they become bureaucrats.\N{\rChinese}于是他们变成官僚。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.88,0:45:25.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They have to prove their worth.\N{\rChinese}好吧？他们得证明自己的价值。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.50,0:45:27.70,English,,0,0,0,,So, they create a lot of paperwork.\N{\rChinese}于是他们产生了大量文件。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.26,0:45:29.70,English,,0,0,0,,They make everyone follow the rules.\N{\rChinese}他们让大家遵守规则。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.04,0:45:33.78,English,,0,0,0,,Society becomes more and more bureaucratic.\N{\rChinese}社会变得越来越官僚化。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.32,0:45:39.48,English,,0,0,0,,Then, in the collapse phase, society becomes\N{\rChinese}随后，在崩溃阶段，社会变得…
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.24,0:45:45.76,English,,0,0,0,,authoritarian. Okay?\N{\rChinese}专制。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.20,0:45:49.36,English,,0,0,0,,Before, decline is about following the rules.\N{\rChinese}之前，衰落是遵守规则。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.18,0:45:52.14,English,,0,0,0,,Now, it's just rule by force.\N{\rChinese}现在，只是用力来统治。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.86,0:45:56.42,English,,0,0,0,,But, there's another way of saying this.\N{\rChinese}但，还有另一种说法。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.78,0:46:00.80,English,,0,0,0,,In the rise phase, what matters is the consent.\N{\rChinese}在崛起阶段，关键是得到同意。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.00,0:46:04.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, these three groups, the elite,\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以，这三组，精英，
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.70,0:46:08.14,English,,0,0,0,,the middle class, and the people, they're all working together\N{\rChinese}中产阶层与百姓，齐心协力，共促社会进步。已获同意。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.82,0:46:10.84,English,,0,0,0,,to improve society. There's consent.\N{\rChinese}但，当你进入衰落阶段，...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.62,0:46:14.58,English,,0,0,0,,But, when you hit the decline phase,\N{\rChinese}But, when you hit the decline phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.18,0:46:19.12,English,,0,0,0,,now, it's the deception. And\N{\rChinese}现在是欺骗。然后，
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.12,0:46:21.38,English,,0,0,0,,then, when you hit the collapse phase, it's coercion.\N{\rChinese}当你进入崛落阶段时是强迫。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.18,0:46:26.24,English,,0,0,0,,So, let me give you an example. Let's just say\N{\rChinese}好了，我给你举个例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.34,0:46:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,we are in the rise phase.\N{\rChinese}我们正处于崛起阶段。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.00,0:46:30.62,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Well, we want to go to lunch.\N{\rChinese}对吧？我们想去吃午饭。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.94,0:46:33.04,English,,0,0,0,,So, we discuss where we go to lunch.\N{\rChinese}于是我们讨论去哪里吃午饭。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.32,0:46:36.36,English,,0,0,0,,I want to go to McDonald's, but you guys want to go to Pizza Hut or KFC.\N{\rChinese}我想去麦当劳，但你们想去必胜客或肯德基。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.72,0:46:39.26,English,,0,0,0,,We have debate, and then, eventually,\N{\rChinese}我们辩论过，随后最终投票，谁想去谁赢。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.72,0:46:44.16,English,,0,0,0,,we vote, and whoever wants to go, the majority wins.\N{\rChinese}投票后，人数多的决定去的地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.28,0:46:45.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's the consent phase.\N{\rChinese}好的？那是同意阶段。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.38,0:46:48.46,English,,0,0,0,,When we hit the decline phase, deception,\N{\rChinese}当我们进入衰落阶段，欺骗，
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.90,0:46:50.16,English,,0,0,0,,I'm the teacher. So, I say to you,\N{\rChinese}我是老师。所以，我对你说，
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.52,0:46:52.80,English,,0,0,0,,let's go to McDonald's because\N{\rChinese}我们去麦当劳吧，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.38,0:46:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,Wong Fei will be there, or Jack Ma will be there, or\N{\rChinese}王飞会在那里，或者马云会在那里，或者
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.10,0:46:59.30,English,,0,0,0,,it's free hamburgers today.\N{\rChinese}今天有免费汉堡。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.52,0:47:02.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? I'm lying to you to get what I want.\N{\rChinese}好的？我在撒谎是为了得到我想要的。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.32,0:47:07.16,English,,0,0,0,,And then, in the collapse phase is, I say to you,\N{\rChinese}然后，在衰落阶段，我对你说，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.20,0:47:09.98,English,,0,0,0,,I'm the teacher, and I will beat you up if you don't listen to me.\N{\rChinese}我是老师，如果你不听我的，我会揍你。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.26,0:47:16.78,English,,0,0,0,,So, in the rise phase,\N{\rChinese}于是，在崛起阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.70,0:47:21.54,English,,0,0,0,,what matters, first and foremost, is unity of the people.\N{\rChinese}首先最重要的是人民的团结。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.76,0:47:23.66,English,,0,0,0,,We're all working together. There's empathy.\N{\rChinese}我们齐心协力，彼此相感。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.06,0:47:25.38,English,,0,0,0,,There's concern for other people.\N{\rChinese}有对他人的关心。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.56,0:47:27.80,English,,0,0,0,,I want to be your friend.\N{\rChinese}我想成为你的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.56,0:47:31.32,English,,0,0,0,,We need to work together to make society better.\N{\rChinese}我们需要一起努力，让社会更好。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.58,0:47:35.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But in the decline phase, it's really about stability.\N{\rChinese}好的？但在衰落阶段，真正是关于稳定。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.10,0:47:38.46,English,,0,0,0,,It's about making sure\N{\rChinese}是关于确保
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.26,0:47:41.84,English,,0,0,0,,that society maintains a status quo.\N{\rChinese}社会保持现状。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.38,0:47:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? When we reach the collapse phase, it is survival.\N{\rChinese}好的？当我们进入崩溃阶段时，就是生存。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.88,0:47:50.90,English,,0,0,0,,Screw you. I want to live,\N{\rChinese}去你个……我想活着。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.02,0:47:54.60,English,,0,0,0,,and if I have to kill you, I'll kill you. Alright?\N{\rChinese}如果我得杀了你，我就杀了你。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.98,0:47:58.16,English,,0,0,0,,So, this is a map that\N{\rChinese}于是，这是一张地图
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.16,0:48:01.56,English,,0,0,0,,shows us what happens when society rises,\N{\rChinese}显示了社会崛起、衰落与崛溃时的变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.00,0:48:03.68,English,,0,0,0,,declines, and collapses.\N{\rChinese}显示了社会崛起、衰落与崛溃时的变化。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.34,0:48:05.98,English,,0,0,0,,Now, what's really interesting about this is\N{\rChinese}现在，真正有趣的地方是
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.84,0:48:10.08,English,,0,0,0,,the timing, okay?\N{\rChinese}时机，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.60,0:48:13.88,English,,0,0,0,,So, if you actually look at\N{\rChinese}于是，如果你真正看一下社会的时间线，它的走势是这样的，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.80,0:48:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,society's timeline, it goes like this, okay?\N{\rChinese}society's timeline, itgoes like this, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.36,0:48:21.98,English,,0,0,0,,It's a steep rise,\N{\rChinese}它是陡峨的上升，下降缓慢，崛溃突发。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.98,0:48:24.92,English,,0,0,0,,the decline is slow, and the collapse is sudden.\N{\rChinese}the decline is slow, andthe collapse is sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.28,0:48:29.90,English,,0,0,0,,So, people think, oh, decline,\N{\rChinese}于是，人们想，哦，衰落，你知道，事物变得更糟，但我们跟着这个趋势，我们还会在这里，实际上，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.32,0:48:32.78,English,,0,0,0,,you know, things get worse, worse, but, you know,\N{\rChinese}你知道，我们跟着这个趋势，我们还会在这里，实际上，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.92,0:48:36.58,English,,0,0,0,,we follow this trend, we'll still be here, but actually,\N{\rChinese}我们跟着这个趋势，我们还会在这里，实际上，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.10,0:48:38.52,English,,0,0,0,,the collapse happens really fast.\N{\rChinese}崩溃发生得很快。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.74,0:48:40.28,English,,0,0,0,,Why? The reason why is,\N{\rChinese}为什么？原因是，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.50,0:48:43.94,English,,0,0,0,,this system cannot survive external shocks.\N{\rChinese}这个体系无法承受外部冲击。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.76,0:48:49.58,English,,0,0,0,,So, external shocks is a perfect storm\N{\rChinese}于是，外部冲击就是一场完美的危机风暴。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.80,0:48:55.50,English,,0,0,0,,of crises. So,\N{\rChinese}于是，另外一种说法是，可能是社会准备的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.60,0:49:00.06,English,,0,0,0,,another way of saying this is maybe society prepares for,\N{\rChinese}another way of saying this is maybe society prepares for,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.18,0:49:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,okay, if there's a plague, we'll do this.\N{\rChinese}好的，若出现瘟疫，我们就这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.16,0:49:05.10,English,,0,0,0,,If there's a climate crisis, we'll do this.\N{\rChinese}若出现气候危机，我们就这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.20,0:49:06.48,English,,0,0,0,,If there's a drought, we'll do this.\N{\rChinese}若出现旱灾，我们就这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.52,0:49:07.74,English,,0,0,0,,If there's a war, we'll do this. Okay?\N{\rChinese}若出现战争，我们就这么做。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.92,0:49:12.06,English,,0,0,0,,What society is not prepared for is these things happening all at once.\N{\rChinese}社会未准备好的就是这些事一次性发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.78,0:49:15.42,English,,0,0,0,,The plague, the drought,\N{\rChinese}瘟疫、旱灾，
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.80,0:49:20.70,English,,0,0,0,,war. So, remember, the revolution, they all happen at once.\N{\rChinese}战争。记住，革命，全部一次发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.80,0:49:24.22,English,,0,0,0,,It's a perfect storm. And that's what leads to the collapse,\N{\rChinese}这是一场完美的风暴。正是它导致了崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.28,0:49:26.66,English,,0,0,0,,because society is not prepared for this.\N{\rChinese}因为社会未准备好。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.30,0:49:30.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And why is society not prepared for this?\N{\rChinese}好吗？那为什么社会没有准备好呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.62,0:49:32.92,English,,0,0,0,,Because when you hit the authoritarian phase,\N{\rChinese}因为当你进入专制阶段，你就不再能批评制度。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.28,0:49:35.62,English,,0,0,0,,you're not allowed to criticize the system anymore.\N{\rChinese}you're not allowed to criticize the system anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.08,0:49:40.12,English,,0,0,0,,The problem are those who speak out.\N{\rChinese}问题在于那些敢发声的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.42,0:49:43.26,English,,0,0,0,,The problem is those who point out the problems of society.\N{\rChinese}问题在于那些指出社会问题的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.12,0:49:49.36,English,,0,0,0,,In the rise phase, those who criticize society are the hearing, the hearers.\N{\rChinese}在崛起阶段，批评社会的人是听者，听者们。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.10,0:49:51.98,English,,0,0,0,,They are appreciated.\N{\rChinese}他们受到赞赏。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.66,0:49:56.74,English,,0,0,0,,They are rewarded. In the collapse phase, those who speak\N{\rChinese}他们得到奖励。在崩溃阶段，发声的人是社会的敌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.36,0:49:59.54,English,,0,0,0,,out are the enemies of society.\N{\rChinese}out are the enemies of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.94,0:50:04.84,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore, society cannot be prepared for any external threats,\N{\rChinese}于是，社会无法为外部威胁做准备，于是导致其崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.02,0:50:06.56,English,,0,0,0,,which leads to its collapse.\N{\rChinese}于是，社会无法为外部威胁做准备，随后导致其崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.94,0:50:14.46,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions? Okay.\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.88,0:50:18.72,English,,0,0,0,,So, this is the ethical model that we're working with.\N{\rChinese}所以，这就是我们正在使用的伦理模型。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.84,0:50:20.62,English,,0,0,0,,And again, we're going to apply it to the present,\N{\rChinese}再一次，我们将把它应用到现在，然后再应用到过去。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.30,0:50:22.74,English,,0,0,0,,and then we're going to apply it to the past.\N{\rChinese}再一次，我们将把它应用到现在，然后再应用到过去。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.78,0:50:25.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, with this ethical model,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，凭借这个伦理模型，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.74,0:50:27.38,English,,0,0,0,,what we can do is make certain predictions\N{\rChinese}我们可以做的就是做出一些预测
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.78,0:50:30.78,English,,0,0,0,,about the future. So, I will make these predictions.\N{\rChinese}关于未来。于是，我会给出这些预测。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.92,0:50:38.90,English,,0,0,0,,And I expect these things to happen in the next\N{\rChinese}我预计这些事将在接下来
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.48,0:50:42.86,English,,0,0,0,,five to ten years.\N{\rChinese}五到十年。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.02,0:50:48.42,English,,0,0,0,,Five to ten years. Or ten to twenty years.\N{\rChinese}五到十年。或十到二十年。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.50,0:50:50.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm not I don't know the time frame.\N{\rChinese}好的，我不知道时间范围。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.38,0:50:51.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But I expect these things to happen.\N{\rChinese}好的？但我预计这些事会发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.80,0:50:55.66,English,,0,0,0,,The first thing that's going to happen in the Western world is\N{\rChinese}第一件事在西方世界将会发生的就是
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.52,0:50:59.98,English,,0,0,0,,decline of democracy and freedom.\N{\rChinese}民主与自由的衰落。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.84,0:51:07.40,English,,0,0,0,,So, remember, in the rise phase,\N{\rChinese}所以，记住，在兴起阶段，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.62,0:51:09.44,English,,0,0,0,,society is democratic and open and meritocratic.\N{\rChinese}社会是民主、开放且以才干为本。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.06,0:51:13.52,English,,0,0,0,,But as you move on, it becomes more bureaucratic and ultimately authoritarian.\N{\rChinese}但随着推进，变得更官僚化，最终成为专制。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.88,0:51:15.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, we will see the United States,\N{\rChinese}好？所以我们将看到美国，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.20,0:51:17.98,English,,0,0,0,,Europe, become much more authoritarian.\N{\rChinese}欧洲，变得更专制。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.28,0:51:22.72,English,,0,0,0,,You will see the collapse of democracy and freedom in these nations.\N{\rChinese}你将看到这些国家的民主与自由崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.56,0:51:26.34,English,,0,0,0,,And already we're seeing this happen in the United States,\N{\rChinese}而且我们已在美国看到这种情况出现，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.50,0:51:30.82,English,,0,0,0,,where Trump is using more and more military to resolve issues.\N{\rChinese}在那里，特朗普越来越多地使用军力来解决问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.14,0:51:35.50,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So, that's the first prediction.\N{\rChinese}对吧？所以，这就是第一个预测。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.80,0:51:38.24,English,,0,0,0,,And this is going to happen throughout the Western world.\N{\rChinese}而且这将在西方世界各地发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.68,0:51:42.42,English,,0,0,0,,Second thing is economic collapse.\N{\rChinese}第二件事是经济崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.26,0:51:49.08,English,,0,0,0,,So, as people have less\N{\rChinese}于是人们的发声权越来越少，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.08,0:51:50.94,English,,0,0,0,,and less right to speak up,\N{\rChinese}他们的发声权越来越少，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.20,0:51:55.02,English,,0,0,0,,they feel less invested in the system, they're less willing to work.\N{\rChinese}他们的发声权越来越少，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.52,0:51:56.88,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you have economic collapse.\N{\rChinese}因此，你们就会出现经济崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.48,0:51:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,People don't believe in the system anymore.\N{\rChinese}人们不再相信这个体系。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.66,0:52:01.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The system is in crisis.\N{\rChinese}好了？体系正陷入危机。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.26,0:52:05.04,English,,0,0,0,,This will lead to immigration.\N{\rChinese}这将导致移民。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.10,0:52:11.04,English,,0,0,0,,The government is like, you know what, if the people don't want to work, screw them.\N{\rChinese}政府会说，明白吧，如果人们不想工作，那就算了。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.16,0:52:14.28,English,,0,0,0,,Let's bring in immigrants to do the work.\N{\rChinese}让我们引进移民来干活。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.54,0:52:17.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This is, let's replace our population.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是，咱们来换人。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.58,0:52:21.98,English,,0,0,0,,But, the people are not going to sit back and take it, right?\N{\rChinese}不过，人们不会坐着等着接受的，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.38,0:52:23.76,English,,0,0,0,,This leads to civil war.\N{\rChinese}这就导致内战。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.06,0:52:30.76,English,,0,0,0,,People are not going to meet each other on the streets.\N{\rChinese}人们不会在街上相遇。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.14,0:52:32.90,English,,0,0,0,,And the government is like, you know what,\N{\rChinese}政府会说，明白吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.76,0:52:36.68,English,,0,0,0,,if we continue to let them fight, eventually\N{\rChinese}如果我们继续让他们打仗，最终
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.04,0:52:41.14,English,,0,0,0,,they're going to come after us. So, what we'll do is send them off to these stupid\N{\rChinese}他们会来追我们。于是我们安排他们去这些傻瓜的海外战争。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.68,0:52:44.32,English,,0,0,0,,pointless wars overseas. Okay?\N{\rChinese}于是你现在有了傻瓜的战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.54,0:52:46.98,English,,0,0,0,,So, now you have stupid wars.\N{\rChinese}So, now you havestupid wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.50,0:52:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,Stupid foreign wars. And\N{\rChinese}傻瓜的海外战争。还有
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.26,0:52:57.78,English,,0,0,0,,these are my five predictions for the world for the next five, ten, twenty years.\N{\rChinese}这些是我对未来五、十、二十年世界的五个预测。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.20,0:53:01.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Europe and America\N{\rChinese}好的？欧洲和美国
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.02,0:53:05.82,English,,0,0,0,,will see less freedom and democracy.\N{\rChinese}将会看到自由与民主的减少。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.16,0:53:08.32,English,,0,0,0,,The people are going to collapse, increase immigration,\N{\rChinese}人们将会崩溃，移民增加，
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.88,0:53:12.34,English,,0,0,0,,civil conflict, and then ultimately stupid foreign wars.\N{\rChinese}内战，随后又是傻瓜的海外战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.56,0:53:13.96,English,,0,0,0,,And I'm not saying this happens\N{\rChinese}我并不是说它们按顺序发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.02,0:53:17.52,English,,0,0,0,,in a sequence.\N{\rChinese}我说的是你会看到这五个阶段全部出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.60,0:53:19.34,English,,0,0,0,,I'm saying you'll see all five phases.\N{\rChinese}我并不是说它们按顺序发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.36,0:53:21.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But they may happen in different order.\N{\rChinese}好的？但它们可能按不同顺序发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.32,0:53:30.14,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions? Once it's clear to you guys.\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？等你们明白后再说。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.22,0:53:33.22,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, thank you. Is there any chance that\N{\rChinese}好的，谢谢。还有机会吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.72,0:53:38.24,English,,0,0,0,,the government tries to use a war to\N{\rChinese}政府试图用战争来做掩护？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.64,0:53:42.38,English,,0,0,0,,distract the people? Like,\N{\rChinese}像是这样，
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.38,0:53:46.86,English,,0,0,0,,they're trying to hide all of the collapse of the society\N{\rChinese}他们正试图掩盖社会崩溃的全部过程。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.86,0:53:48.40,English,,0,0,0,,and their country. Yeah.\N{\rChinese}和他们的国家。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.46,0:53:50.12,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's a great question.\N{\rChinese}好的。很好的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.28,0:53:52.14,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer is, that's what wars are for.\N{\rChinese}答案是，战争正是为此而生。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.52,0:53:53.86,English,,0,0,0,,It's to distract the people, right?\N{\rChinese}把它用来掩盖人们的注意力，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.08,0:53:57.46,English,,0,0,0,,Because if you don't distract the people, they'll come and revolt against you.\N{\rChinese}如果不掩盖人们，他们就会来起义。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.46,0:54:03.14,English,,0,0,0,,So, you either send them to a war or you could have a French Revolution on your hands.\N{\rChinese}所以，你要么把他们送去战争，要么让他们在你手里掀起法国大革命。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.90,0:54:05.74,English,,0,0,0,,Right? That's your option. War or revolution?\N{\rChinese}对吗？那是你的选择。战争还是革命？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.02,0:54:07.24,English,,0,0,0,,I think war is the better option.\N{\rChinese}我觉得战争是更好的选择。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.16,0:54:10.70,English,,0,0,0,,That's why we're heading into a world at war.\N{\rChinese}这就是我们进入战争世界的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.32,0:54:15.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, no, no.\N{\rChinese}好的，没错，没错。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.50,0:54:17.56,English,,0,0,0,,I'm saying like, if you don't send the people to war,\N{\rChinese}我说的是，如果你不把人们送去战争，
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.78,0:54:22.46,English,,0,0,0,,so you send them off to war to distract them.\N{\rChinese}于是你把他们送去战争来掩盖他们。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.74,0:54:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,To get rid of them. Okay,\N{\rChinese}把他们去掉。好，
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.26,0:54:32.24,English,,0,0,0,,there's no right and wrong here, okay? Okay, alright.\N{\rChinese}这里没有对错，好的，好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.54,0:54:36.88,English,,0,0,0,,I apologize, okay? But one thing that you will learn in my class is, there's no right\N{\rChinese}我道歉，好的？但你会在我的课上学到的一件事是，没有对。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.54,0:54:39.22,English,,0,0,0,,and wrong. There's no logic.\N{\rChinese}还有错。没有逻辑。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.46,0:54:41.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It's not like,\N{\rChinese}好？不是这样，
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.38,0:54:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,it is immoral to send people to war.\N{\rChinese}把人送去战争是非道德的。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.44,0:54:47.94,English,,0,0,0,,I know that. Thank you very much. Okay, but I'm trying to explain to you how power works.\N{\rChinese}我知道。非常感谢。好了，我正试着向你解释权力的运作方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.34,0:54:52.36,English,,0,0,0,,That's the theme of this class. I'm trying to explain to you how people in power think and behave.\N{\rChinese}这就是本课的主题。我正试着向你解释掌权者的思维与行为。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.34,0:54:57.04,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? And, again, I keep on saying this.\N{\rChinese}好了？再说一次，我一直在说这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.14,0:54:58.52,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I'm right.\N{\rChinese}我不知道自己是否正确。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.58,0:55:04.04,English,,0,0,0,,But what I'm doing is, I'm presenting a theory, a model that we can use\N{\rChinese}我现在做的是提出一个理论，一个我们可以用来做预测的模型。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.02,0:55:06.28,English,,0,0,0,,to make predictions.\N{\rChinese}to make predictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.66,0:55:10.44,English,,0,0,0,,And if these predictions work out, if it actually happens, then our model,\N{\rChinese}如果这些预测落地，真的发生了，那么我们的模型就有一定准确性。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.18,0:55:12.64,English,,0,0,0,,there's some accuracy to our model.\N{\rChinese}模型有一定准确性。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.74,0:55:15.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We'll have to refine our model, but there's some accuracy to it.\N{\rChinese}好的？我们会进一步完善模型，但它已经有一定准确性。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.80,0:55:19.58,English,,0,0,0,,But hey, if tomorrow, Trump, Putin,\N{\rChinese}但如果明天，特朗普、普京、习一起说，咱们做最好的朋友，那我就错了。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.04,0:55:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,Xi, all get together and say, let's be best friends,\N{\rChinese}但如果明天，特朗普、普京、习一起说，咱们做最好的朋友，那我就错了。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.18,0:55:26.38,English,,0,0,0,,then I'm wrong.\N{\rChinese}但如果明天，特朗普、普京、习一起说，咱们做最好的朋友，那我就错了。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.70,0:55:29.68,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Okay?\N{\rChinese}对吧？好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.80,0:55:31.28,English,,0,0,0,,So that's what we're trying to do in this class.\N{\rChinese}所以这就是我们在这门课里要做的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.40,0:55:35.88,English,,0,0,0,,We're not trying to argue what is right, what is wrong, what is just.\N{\rChinese}我们不是在争论什么是对的、错的、正义的。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.54,0:55:38.96,English,,0,0,0,,Because, quite honestly, it doesn't matter.\N{\rChinese}因为，坦白说，没什么大不了的。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.94,0:55:42.00,English,,0,0,0,,Morality doesn't matter here. It's about power.\N{\rChinese}道德在这里不重要，关键是权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.18,0:55:46.26,English,,0,0,0,,We're trying to understand how the world works.\N{\rChinese}我们要弄懂世界是怎么运作的。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.76,0:55:51.44,English,,0,0,0,,And if we do that, then maybe we can work together\N{\rChinese}如果我们这么做，或许我们能一起合作
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.79,0:55:53.60,English,,0,0,0,,and build a more just world.\N{\rChinese}并且建造一个更公正的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.28,0:55:57.24,English,,0,0,0,,But first we need to figure out how the world really, really works.\N{\rChinese}但首先我们得弄清世界到底是怎样运作的
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.02,0:55:59.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Any more questions?\N{\rChinese}好的？还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.24,0:56:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Great, guys.\N{\rChinese}好的。太好了，大家。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.76,0:56:09.44,English,,0,0,0,,So we will continue this story\N{\rChinese}于是我们继续这个故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.87,0:56:11.94,English,,0,0,0,,next class. I'll see you guys next class.\N{\rChinese}下节课见。下节课再见。
